emclaw is 2.4.0.\",\n\n  Line 134:         note=\"``running_version`` is single-valued.\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/mcp_server.py:\n  Line 28: from common.enrichment.constants import SERVER_RESERVED_MEMORY_TYPES\n\n  Line 395:         \"Memories are auto-enriched with type, title, summary, and tags via LLM. \"\n\n  Line 1283:                 # Resolve which string in `data` gets embedded. The only\n\n  Line 1284:                 # embeddable field is data[\"summary\"]; skills writes also\n\n  Line 1286:                 # writes without a summary store cleanly with no embedding\n\n  Line 1290:                     resolve_embed_source,\n\n  Line 1294:                     source = resolve_embed_source(collection, data)\n\n  Line 1297:                 embedding: list[float] | None = None\n\n  Line 1299:                     from common.embedding import get_embedding\n\n  Line 1301:                     embedding = await get_embedding(source)\n\n  Line 1302:                     if embedding is None:\n\n  Line 1323:                     embedding=embedding,\n\n  Line 1341:                             \"indexed\": embedding is not None,\n\n  Line 1397:                 from common.embedding import get_embedding\n\n  Line 1399:                 query_embedding = await get_embedding(query)\n\n  Line 1400:                 if query_embedding is None:\n\n  Line 1414:                     query_embedding=query_embedding,\n\n  Line 1797:             description=\"contradictions|failures|stale|divergence|patterns|discover.\",\n\n  Line 1804:     \"\"\"Analyze the memory store for patterns, contradictions, stale knowledge,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/lifecycle.py:\n  Line 15:     archive_stale,\n\n  Line 26:     async def archive_stale(self, *, org_id: str, fleet_id: str | None) -> int:\n\n  Line 27:         return await archive_stale(get_storage_client(), tenant_id=org_id, fleet_id=fleet_id)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/scripts/latency_test.py:\n  Line 32:     \"The ML team trained a new embedding model — recall@10 improved from 0.82 to 0.91 on the internal benchmark.\",\n\n  Line 41:     \"The onboarding flow conversion rate increased from 23% to 31% after removing the email verification step.\",\n\n  Line 158:     # Small pause to let embeddings settle\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/lifecycle_handlers.py:\n  Line 48:     async def archive_stale(self, *, org_id: str, fleet_id: str | None) -> int: ...\n\n  Line 268:     async def archive_stale_op(req: LifecycleArchiveRequest) -> int:\n\n  Line 269:         return await adapter.archive_stale(org_id=req.org_id, fleet_id=req.fleet_id)\n\n  Line 296:             run_op=archive_stale_op,\n\n  Line 298:             action=\"archive-stale\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/scripts/repro_contradictions_not_detected.py:\n  Line 15:     4. Wait N seconds for background enrichment + entity extraction +\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/config.py:\n  Line 21:     # Storage backend — the worker PATCHes embeddings to core-storage-api\n\n  Line 38:     # Per-tenant cap on concurrent storage PATCH-backs (embed/enrich\n\n  Line 43:     # PATCHes per write (embed + enrich); without this cap one\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/tests/test_identity_token.py:\n  Line 120:     metadata server rather than return the stale cached token.\"\"\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_embedded_publisher.py:\n  Line 9: Mirrors :func:`common.events.memory_enriched_publisher.publish_memory_enriched`\n\n  Line 10: in shape; consumed by ``core-api``'s ``handle_memory_embedded`` to\n\n  Line 11: fire post-embed contradiction detection.\n\n  Line 20: from common.events.memory_embedded import MemoryEmbedded\n\n  Line 24: async def publish_memory_embedded(\n\n  Line 30:     \"\"\"Announce successful embedding of *memory_id*.\n\n  Line 34:     ``handle_embed_request``) wraps in tracking so a transport error\n\n  Line 36:     succeeded — the embedding is durable in storage either way, this\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_enriched.py:\n  Line 1: \"\"\"Typed payload for the ``memclaw.memory.enriched`` topic (CAURA-595).\n\n  Line 3: Counterpart to :class:`~common.events.memory_enrich_request.MemoryEnrichRequest`:\n\n  Line 4: core-worker emits one of these *after* successfully PATCHing enrichment\n\n  Line 6: effects — primarily a hint-driven re-embed when the LLM produced a\n\n  Line 7: ``retrieval_hint`` that would beat the raw-content embedding's\n\n  Line 12: ``_validate_enrichment``). The full ``EnrichmentResult`` is *not*\n\n  Line 15: Empty / missing ``retrieval_hint`` is a signal that no re-embed is\n\n  Line 16: warranted (heuristic-fallback enrichments, content-already-query-aligned\n\n  Line 31:     \"\"\"Announce a successful enrichment of a memory row.\"\"\"\n\n  Line 48:     # Empty string when the enricher produced no useful hint —\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/consumer.py:\n  Line 1: \"\"\"Async-embed and async-enrich event consumers.\n\n  Line 6:   :class:`~common.events.memory_embed_request.MemoryEmbedRequest`,\n\n  Line 7:   resolves the embedding via the platform-tier provider, PATCHes it\n\n  Line 10:   :class:`~common.events.memory_enrich_request.MemoryEnrichRequest`,\n\n  Line 12:   :func:`common.enrichment.enrich_memory` (3-tier provider fallback),\n\n  Line 19:    embedding for the same ``content_hash``, reuse it and skip the\n\n  Line 21: 3. Otherwise call the platform-tier embedding provider via\n\n  Line 22:    :func:`common.embedding.get_platform_embedding`.\n\n  Line 23: 4. PATCH the embedding back onto the memory row via core-storage-api.\n\n  Line 26: event re-PATCHes the row with the (deterministic) same embedding.\n\n  Line 35: * ``get_platform_embedding() is None`` (PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_* not\n\n  Line 53: from common.embedding import get_platform_embedding\n\n  Line 54: from common.enrichment import EnrichmentResult, enrich_memory\n\n  Line 57: from common.events.memory_embed_request import MemoryEmbedRequest\n\n  Line 58: from common.events.memory_embedded_publisher import publish_memory_embedded\n\n  Line 59: from common.events.memory_enrich_request import MemoryEnrichRequest\n\n  Line 60: from common.events.memory_enriched_publisher import publish_memory_enriched\n\n  Line 67:     find_embedding_by_content_hash,\n\n  Line 68:     update_memory_embedding,\n\n  Line 69:     update_memory_enrichment,\n\n  Line 96: async def handle_embed_request(event: Event) -> None:\n\n  Line 97:     \"\"\"Process a single embed-request event.\"\"\"\n\n  Line 105:             \"dropping malformed embed-request payload\",\n\n  Line 119:             \"dropping embed-request: consumer not configured\",\n\n  Line 128:     provider = get_platform_embedding()\n\n  Line 131:             \"dropping embed-request: PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_* unset, no platform embedding singleton configured\",\n\n  Line 142:     embedding: list[float] | None = None\n\n  Line 147:         embedding = await find_embedding_by_content_hash(\n\n  Line 152:         if embedding is not None:\n\n  Line 154:                 \"reusing cached embedding for content_hash\",\n\n  Line 162:     if embedding is None:\n\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 4632 matches (4532 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":4632,"truncated":true},"title":"chunk|embed|reembed|re-embed|enrich|version|model_version|fingerprint|dirty|stale","time":{"start":1780728082851,"end":1780728082994}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0561695d1d534f25016a23c111a39481939f95084fcff5f597"}},"id":"prt_e9baa2d4d0012XhgYrXDYKq9pH","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9ba9fa050014HOER5jZVd3Lrg"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780728083311,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"id":"prt_e9baa336d001tUUWhb8E9nVCsw","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"0b857771954b00b4141186e91b60811dfd95680f","messageID":"msg_e9ba9fa050014HOER5jZVd3Lrg","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":44027,"input":22493,"output":510,"reasoning":32,"cache":{"write":0,"read":20992}},"cost":0}}
