{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728096240,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OAuGO1akFFM1zdMnAx2gHKZ1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/consumer.py","offset":1,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/consumer.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Async-embed and async-enrich event consumers.\n2: \n3: Subscribes to:\n4: \n5: * ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED`` (CAURA-594) — one\n6:   :class:`~common.events.memory_embed_request.MemoryEmbedRequest`,\n7:   resolves the embedding via the platform-tier provider, PATCHes it\n8:   back onto the memory row.\n9: * ``Topics.Memory.ENRICH_REQUESTED`` (CAURA-595) — one\n10:   :class:`~common.events.memory_enrich_request.MemoryEnrichRequest`,\n11:   reconstructs the tenant config from the payload, runs\n12:   :func:`common.enrichment.enrich_memory` (3-tier provider fallback),\n13:   and PATCHes the resulting fields back onto the memory row.\n14: \n15: Embed-request flow (existing):\n16: \n17: 1. Validate the envelope's payload as ``MemoryEmbedRequest``.\n18: 2. Cache lookup: if any other row in the tenant already has an\n19:    embedding for the same ``content_hash``, reuse it and skip the\n20:    provider call.\n21: 3. Otherwise call the platform-tier embedding provider via\n22:    :func:`common.embedding.get_platform_embedding`.\n23: 4. PATCH the embedding back onto the memory row via core-storage-api.\n24: \n25: Idempotency: at-least-once delivery from Pub/Sub means a redelivered\n26: event re-PATCHes the row with the (deterministic) same embedding.\n27: That's safe — the storage update is a write-after-write of the same\n28: column. ``content_hash`` cache lookup keeps the redelivery cost down\n29: to a single GET in the steady-state.\n30: \n31: Failure modes:\n32: * ``ValidationError`` on a bad payload → ack + drop (poison-message\n33:   guard; matches the platform-audit-api pattern). The DLQ provisioned\n34:   by the bootstrap script catches anything we miss.\n35: * ``get_platform_embedding() is None`` (PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_* not\n36:   configured) → log + ack-drop. The worker is platform-only by\n37:   design; without the singleton there's nothing it can do, and\n38:   raising would just hot-loop redeliveries.\n39: * Provider exception or storage PATCH failure → raise → nack →\n40:   Pub/Sub redelivers (subject to max-delivery-attempts → DLQ).\n41: \"\"\"\n42: \n43: from __future__ import annotations\n44: \n45: import logging\n46: from collections.abc import Callable\n47: from datetime import datetime\n48: from types import SimpleNamespace\n49: \n50: import httpx\n51: from pydantic import ValidationError\n52: \n53: from common.embedding import get_platform_embedding\n54: from common.enrichment import EnrichmentResult, enrich_memory\n55: from common.events.base import Event\n56: from common.events.factory import get_event_bus\n57: from common.events.memory_embed_request import MemoryEmbedRequest\n58: from common.events.memory_embedded_publisher import publish_memory_embedded\n59: from common.events.memory_enrich_request import MemoryEnrichRequest\n60: from common.events.memory_enriched_publisher import publish_memory_enriched\n61: from common.events.suppression_handlers import (\n62:     SuppressionStorageAdapter,\n63:     register_suppression_consumer,\n64: )\n65: from common.events.topics import Topics\n66: from core_worker.clients.storage_client import (\n67:     find_embedding_by_content_hash,\n68:     update_memory_embedding,\n69:     update_memory_enrichment,\n70:     upsert_tenant_suppression,\n71: )\n72: from core_worker.per_tenant_concurrency import per_tenant_storage_slot\n73: \n74: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n75: \n76: # Zero-arg factory so the consumer doesn't have to plumb Settings on\n77: # every event. The storage_client module reads its own Settings on\n78: # first call (singleton). Tests inject a stub by overriding this\n79: # variable directly via ``configure``.\n80: StorageClientFactory = Callable[[], httpx.AsyncClient]\n81: \n82: _storage_client_factory: StorageClientFactory | None = None\n83: \n84: \n85: def configure(storage_client_factory: StorageClientFactory) -> None:\n86:     \"\"\"Bind the per-process state the consumer needs.\n87: \n88:     Called once at app startup before ``register_consumers`` /\n89:     ``bus.start()``. ``storage_client_factory`` is a zero-arg callable\n90:     returning the shared httpx client (so tests can inject a stub).\n91:     \"\"\"\n92:     global _storage_client_factory\n93:     _storage_client_factory = storage_client_factory\n94: \n95: \n96: async def handle_embed_request(event: Event) -> None:\n97:     \"\"\"Process a single embed-request event.\"\"\"\n98:     try:\n99:         request = MemoryEmbedRequest(**event.payload)\n100:     except ValidationError:\n101:         # Schema-drift / malformed payload. Log loudly with the\n102:         # ``dropped=True`` alert hook (matches platform-audit-api) and\n103:         # ack-drop so the subscription doesn't loop on a poison message.\n104:         logger.exception(\n105:             \"dropping malformed embed-request payload\",\n106:             extra={\n107:                 \"event_type\": event.event_type,\n108:                 \"event_id\": str(event.event_id),\n109:                 \"dropped\": True,\n110:             },\n111:         )\n112:         return\n113: \n114:     if _storage_client_factory is None:\n115:         # Startup ordering bug — configure() was never called. Drop with\n116:         # a loud log (raising would nack-loop at full Pub/Sub throughput\n117:         # against a permanently misconfigured pod).\n118:         logger.error(\n119:             \"dropping embed-request: consumer not configured\",\n120:             extra={\n121:                 \"event_id\": str(event.event_id),\n122:                 \"memory_id\": str(request.memory_id),\n123:                 \"dropped\": True,\n124:             },\n125:         )\n126:         return\n127: \n128:     provider = get_platform_embedding()\n129:     if provider is None:\n130:         logger.error(\n131:             \"dropping embed-request: PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_* unset, no platform embedding singleton configured\",\n132:             extra={\n133:                 \"event_id\": str(event.event_id),\n134:                 \"memory_id\": str(request.memory_id),\n135:                 \"dropped\": True,\n136:             },\n137:         )\n138:         return\n139: \n140:     storage = _storage_client_factory()\n141: \n142:     embedding: list[float] | None = None\n143: \n144:     # Step 1 — content-hash cache lookup. Saves one provider call on\n145:     # redeliveries and on legitimate within-tenant duplicates.\n146:     if request.content_hash:\n147:         embedding = await find_embedding_by_content_hash(\n148:             storage,\n149:             tenant_id=request.tenant_id,\n150:             content_hash=request.content_hash,\n151:         )\n152:         if embedding is not None:\n153:             logger.info(\n154:                 \"reusing cached embedding for content_hash\",\n155:                 extra={\n156:                     \"memory_id\": str(request.memory_id),\n157:                     \"tenant_id\": request.tenant_id,\n158:                 },\n159:             )\n160: \n161:     # Step 2 — provider call (skipped on cache hit).\n162:     if embedding is None:\n163:         embedding = await provider.embed(request.content)\n164: \n165:     # Step 3 — persist. Raises on non-2xx → nacks → redelivers.\n166:     # Per-tenant slot scoped to the PATCH roundtrip only, so a\n167:     # tenant-A storm can't park every storage-writer connection here\n168:     # while tenant B's lone PATCH queues behind. Provider call above\n169:     # stays unguarded — that's the expensive step and it doesn't\n170:     # touch the storage-writer pool.\n171:     async with per_tenant_storage_slot(request.tenant_id):\n172:         await update_memory_embedding(\n173:             storage,\n174:             memory_id=request.memory_id,\n175:             tenant_id=request.tenant_id,\n176:             embedding=embedding,\n177:         )\n178: \n179:     # Back-channel: announce successful embed so core-api can fire\n180:     # post-embed contradiction detection. Closes the documented\n181:     # ``handle_memory_enriched`` gap that silently dropped detection\n182:     # whenever enrichment landed before embedding (the only case under\n183:     # ``EMBED_ON_HOT_PATH=false``). Best-effort — a publish failure\n184:     # MUST NOT nack the upstream PATCH that already succeeded; the\n185:     # embedding is durable in storage either way.\n186:     try:\n187:         await publish_memory_embedded(\n188:             memory_id=request.memory_id,\n189:             tenant_id=request.tenant_id,\n190:             content=request.content,\n191:         )\n192:     except Exception:\n193:         logger.exception(\n194:             \"embedded back-channel publish failed; ack-continuing\",\n195:             extra={\n196:                 \"memory_id\": str(request.memory_id),\n197:                 \"tenant_id\": request.tenant_id,\n198:             },\n199:         )\n200: \n201:     logger.info(\n202:         \"embed-request processed\",\n203:         extra={\n204:             \"memory_id\": str(request.memory_id),\n205:             \"tenant_id\": request.tenant_id,\n206:             \"provider\": provider.provider_name,\n207:             \"model\": provider.model,\n208:         },\n209:     )\n210: \n211: \n212: # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n213: # Enrich-request consumer (CAURA-595)\n214: # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n215: \n216: \n217: # ORM column fields the worker writes directly. Stays in sync with the\n218: # corresponding ``Memory`` columns + the synchronous-path mapping in\n219: # ``core_api.services.memory_service``. Anything an ``EnrichmentResult``\n220: # field would write to but isn't here lands in ``metadata_patch`` below.\n221: _ENRICHMENT_ORM_FIELDS: frozenset[str] = frozenset(\n222:     {\n223:         \"memory_type\",\n224:         \"weight\",\n225:         \"title\",\n226:         \"status\",\n227:         \"ts_valid_start\",\n228:         \"ts_valid_end\",\n229:     }\n230: )\n231: \n232: # Enrichment fields that live in ``Memory.metadata`` JSONB. Synchronous\n233: # path (``memory_service.py``) writes them as ``metadata[\"summary\"]``,\n234: # ``metadata[\"tags\"]``, etc.; the worker mirrors that via the storage\n235: # layer's atomic ``metadata_patch`` JSONB merge.\n236: _ENRICHMENT_METADATA_FIELDS: frozenset[str] = frozenset(\n237:     {\n238:         \"summary\",\n239:         \"tags\",\n240:         \"contains_pii\",\n241:         \"pii_types\",\n242:         \"retrieval_hint\",\n243:         \"llm_ms\",\n244:     }\n245: )\n246: \n247: # ``EnrichmentResult`` fields the worker INTENTIONALLY does not route\n248: # to storage. Listed explicitly so the exhaustive-routing assert below\n249: # fails when a future field is added without a code site to handle it\n250: # — silent drops are the failure mode we're guarding against.\n251: #\n252: # ``atomic_facts``: the synchronous write path fans these out into\n253: # child memories; the async worker doesn't yet implement that — see\n254: # the ``logger.debug`` in ``handle_enrich_request`` that surfaces the\n255: # gap when an enrichment produces them.\n256: _ENRICHMENT_UNROUTED_FIELDS: frozenset[str] = frozenset({\"atomic_facts\"})\n257: \n258: # Metadata fields that ALWAYS overwrite (when not ``None`` and the\n259: # result came from a real LLM call — see the ``llm_ms > 0`` guard at\n260: # the call site) so a re-delivery / second-LLM-run can clear stale\n261: # state from an earlier write. JSONB ``||`` merge treats ``False`` /\n262: # ``\"\"`` / ``[]`` as ordinary values and overwrites keyed entries.\n263: #\n264: # * ``contains_pii`` / ``pii_types`` — non-deterministic LLM output;\n265: #   an earlier ``contains_pii=True`` must be clearable.\n266: # * ``retrieval_hint`` — the prompt explicitly instructs the LLM to\n267: #   return ``\"\"`` for content that's already query-aligned; without\n268: #   always-write a re-enrichment that drops the hint would leave\n269: #   metadata stale AND the embedding still prefix-augmented.\n270: # * ``tags`` — the prompt instructs the LLM to always populate 2-6\n271: #   tags. ``tags=[]`` from a real LLM run means \"no tags\" intentionally\n272: #   and must overwrite a prior non-empty list.\n273: # * ``summary`` — without the guard, a heuristic-fallback redelivery\n274: #   would write ``fake_enrich``'s ``summary=content[:200]`` over a\n275: #   prior quality LLM summary. The truncation is a non-empty string,\n276: #   so the ``value in (False, 0, \"\", [])`` skip-check below doesn't\n277: #   catch it. Pairing summary with the ``llm_ms > 0`` guard ensures\n278: #   only real-LLM summaries can overwrite (or clear, if the LLM\n279: #   returns ``\"\"``).\n280: _ENRICHMENT_ALWAYS_WRITE_METADATA: frozenset[str] = frozenset(\n281:     {\"contains_pii\", \"pii_types\", \"retrieval_hint\", \"summary\", \"tags\"}\n282: )\n283: \n284: # Defence-in-depth: a typo in the tuples above would silently drop in\n285: # the storage layer's ``hasattr(Memory, key)`` filter, *and* a future\n286: # ``EnrichmentResult`` field that no one wires to a routing tuple\n287: # would silently fall on the floor. Catch both at module import.\n288: _unrouted = (\n289:     set(EnrichmentResult.model_fields)\n290:     - _ENRICHMENT_ORM_FIELDS\n291:     - _ENRICHMENT_METADATA_FIELDS\n292:     - _ENRICHMENT_UNROUTED_FIELDS\n293: )\n294: # Raise rather than ``assert`` — ``python -O`` strips assertions, and\n295: # this guard's whole point is to surface routing-table drift on every\n296: # import in every environment. Matches\n297: # ``_assert_override_fields_match_schemas`` in ``memory_service.py``.\n298: if _unrouted:\n299:     raise RuntimeError(\n300:         f\"EnrichmentResult fields not routed to storage by handle_enrich_request: \"\n301:         f\"{sorted(_unrouted)} — add to one of _ENRICHMENT_ORM_FIELDS / \"\n302:         f\"_ENRICHMENT_METADATA_FIELDS / _ENRICHMENT_UNROUTED_FIELDS\"\n303:     )\n304: del _unrouted\n305: \n306: \n307: def _build_tenant_config(request: MemoryEnrichRequest) -> SimpleNamespace | None:\n308:     \"\"\"Reconstruct a duck-typed tenant_config from the event payload.\n309: \n310:     ``common.enrichment.service.enrich_memory`` only reads attributes\n311:     off ``tenant_config``; a ``SimpleNamespace`` matching that surface is\n312:     enough — no need to import ``ResolvedConfig``.\n313: \n314:     Returns ``None`` only when the payload genuinely carries no\n315:     tenant-specific config — neither a provider preference nor any API\n316:     keys. The early-return on ``enrichment_provider is None`` alone\n317:     would silently discard a tenant's keys, making the async path\n318:     behave differently from the sync path: sync sees\n319:     ``provider=None`` and defaults to ``\"openai\"`` while still using\n320:     the tenant's ``openai_api_key``; async would fall through to the\n321:     platform-tier provider or the heuristic. The check below mirrors\n322:     sync semantics — if any credential is present we build the\n323:     namespace with ``enrichment_provider=None`` and let\n324:     :func:`enrich_memory` apply its ``or ProviderName.OPENAI``\n325:     default.\n326:     \"\"\"\n327:     has_any_credentials = any(\n328:         (\n329:             request.openai_api_key,\n330:             request.anthropic_api_key,\n331:             request.openrouter_api_key,\n332:             request.gemini_api_key,\n333:         )\n334:     )\n335:     if request.enrichment_provider is None and not has_any_credentials:\n336:         return None\n337: \n338:     fb_provider = request.fallback_provider\n339:     fb_model = request.fallback_model\n340: \n341:     def resolve_fallback() -> tuple[str | None, str | None]:\n342:         return fb_provider, fb_model\n343: \n344:     return SimpleNamespace(\n345:         enrichment_provider=request.enrichment_provider,\n346:         enrichment_model=request.enrichment_model,\n347:         openai_api_key=request.openai_api_key,\n348:         anthropic_api_key=request.anthropic_api_key,\n349:         openrouter_api_key=request.openrouter_api_key,\n350:         gemini_api_key=request.gemini_api_key,\n351:         # Synthesised callable matches the\n352:         # ``ResolvedConfig.resolve_fallback()`` shape ``call_with_fallback``\n353:         # expects. The publisher already pre-resolved the tuple at\n354:         # publish time so the worker doesn't run the policy itself.\n355:         resolve_fallback=resolve_fallback,\n356:     )\n357: \n358: \n359: def _build_patch(\n360:     result: EnrichmentResult,\n\n(Showing lines 1-360 of 625. Use offset=361 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Async-embed and async-enrich event consumers.\n\nSubscribes to:\n\n* ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED`` (CAURA-594) — one\n  :class:`~common.events.memory_embed_request.MemoryEmbedRequest`,\n  resolves the embedding via the platform-tier provider, PATCHes it\n  back onto the memory row.\n* ``Topics.Memory.ENRICH_REQUESTED`` (CAURA-595) — one\n  :class:`~common.events.memory_enrich_request.MemoryEnrichRequest`,\n  reconstructs the tenant config from the payload, runs\n  :func:`common.enrichment.enrich_memory` (3-tier provider fallback),\n  and PATCHes the resulting fields back onto the memory row.\n\nEmbed-request flow (existing):\n\n1. Validate the envelope's payload as ``MemoryEmbedRequest``.\n2. Cache lookup: if any other row in the tenant already has an\n   embedding for the same ``content_hash``, reuse it and skip the\n   provider call.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/consumer.py","text":"\"\"\"Async-embed and async-enrich event consumers.\n\nSubscribes to:\n\n* ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED`` (CAURA-594) — one\n  :class:`~common.events.memory_embed_request.MemoryEmbedRequest`,\n  resolves the embedding via the platform-tier provider, PATCHes it\n  back onto the memory row.\n* ``Topics.Memory.ENRICH_REQUESTED`` (CAURA-595) — one\n  :class:`~common.events.memory_enrich_request.MemoryEnrichRequest`,\n  reconstructs the tenant config from the payload, runs\n  :func:`common.enrichment.enrich_memory` (3-tier provider fallback),\n  and PATCHes the resulting fields back onto the memory row.\n\nEmbed-request flow (existing):\n\n1. Validate the envelope's payload as ``MemoryEmbedRequest``.\n2. Cache lookup: if any other row in the tenant already has an\n   embedding for the same ``content_hash``, reuse it and skip the\n   provider call.\n3. Otherwise call the platform-tier embedding provider via\n   :func:`common.embedding.get_platform_embedding`.\n4. PATCH the embedding back onto the memory row via core-storage-api.\n\nIdempotency: at-least-once delivery from Pub/Sub means a redelivered\nevent re-PATCHes the row with the (deterministic) same embedding.\nThat's safe — the storage update is a write-after-write of the same\ncolumn. ``content_hash`` cache lookup keeps the redelivery cost down\nto a single GET in the steady-state.\n\nFailure modes:\n* ``ValidationError`` on a bad payload → ack + drop (poison-message\n  guard; matches the platform-audit-api pattern). The DLQ provisioned\n  by the bootstrap script catches anything we miss.\n* ``get_platform_embedding() is None`` (PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_* not\n  configured) → log + ack-drop. The worker is platform-only by\n  design; without the singleton there's nothing it can do, and\n  raising would just hot-loop redeliveries.\n* Provider exception or storage PATCH failure → raise → nack →\n  Pub/Sub redelivers (subject to max-delivery-attempts → DLQ).\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom collections.abc import Callable\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom types import SimpleNamespace\n\nimport httpx\nfrom pydantic import ValidationError\n\nfrom common.embedding import get_platform_embedding\nfrom common.enrichment import EnrichmentResult, enrich_memory\nfrom common.events.base import Event\nfrom common.events.factory import get_event_bus\nfrom common.events.memory_embed_request import MemoryEmbedRequest\nfrom common.events.memory_embedded_publisher import publish_memory_embedded\nfrom common.events.memory_enrich_request import MemoryEnrichRequest\nfrom common.events.memory_enriched_publisher import publish_memory_enriched\nfrom common.events.suppression_handlers import (\n    SuppressionStorageAdapter,\n    register_suppression_consumer,\n)\nfrom common.events.topics import Topics\nfrom core_worker.clients.storage_client import (\n    find_embedding_by_content_hash,\n    update_memory_embedding,\n    update_memory_enrichment,\n    upsert_tenant_suppression,\n)\nfrom core_worker.per_tenant_concurrency import per_tenant_storage_slot\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n# Zero-arg factory so the consumer doesn't have to plumb Settings on\n# every event. The storage_client module reads its own Settings on\n# first call (singleton). Tests inject a stub by overriding this\n# variable directly via ``configure``.\nStorageClientFactory = Callable[[], httpx.AsyncClient]\n\n_storage_client_factory: StorageClientFactory | None = None\n\n\ndef configure(storage_client_factory: StorageClientFactory) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Bind the per-process state the consumer needs.\n\n    Called once at app startup before ``register_consumers`` /\n    ``bus.start()``. ``storage_client_factory`` is a zero-arg callable\n    returning the shared httpx client (so tests can inject a stub).\n    \"\"\"\n    global _storage_client_factory\n    _storage_client_factory = storage_client_factory\n\n\nasync def handle_embed_request(event: Event) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Process a single embed-request event.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        request = MemoryEmbedRequest(**event.payload)\n    except ValidationError:\n        # Schema-drift / malformed payload. Log loudly with the\n        # ``dropped=True`` alert hook (matches platform-audit-api) and\n        # ack-drop so the subscription doesn't loop on a poison message.\n        logger.exception(\n            \"dropping malformed embed-request payload\",\n            extra={\n                \"event_type\": event.event_type,\n                \"event_id\": str(event.event_id),\n                \"dropped\": True,\n            },\n        )\n        return\n\n    if _storage_client_factory is None:\n        # Startup ordering bug — configure() was never called. Drop with\n        # a loud log (raising would nack-loop at full Pub/Sub throughput\n        # against a permanently misconfigured pod).\n        logger.error(\n            \"dropping embed-request: consumer not configured\",\n            extra={\n                \"event_id\": str(event.event_id),\n                \"memory_id\": str(request.memory_id),\n                \"dropped\": True,\n            },\n        )\n        return\n\n    provider = get_platform_embedding()\n    if provider is None:\n        logger.error(\n            \"dropping embed-request: PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_* unset, no platform embedding singleton configured\",\n            extra={\n                \"event_id\": str(event.event_id),\n                \"memory_id\": str(request.memory_id),\n                \"dropped\": True,\n            },\n        )\n        return\n\n    storage = _storage_client_factory()\n\n    embedding: list[float] | None = None\n\n    # Step 1 — content-hash cache lookup. Saves one provider call on\n    # redeliveries and on legitimate within-tenant duplicates.\n    if request.content_hash:\n        embedding = await find_embedding_by_content_hash(\n            storage,\n            tenant_id=request.tenant_id,\n            content_hash=request.content_hash,\n        )\n        if embedding is not None:\n            logger.info(\n                \"reusing cached embedding for content_hash\",\n                extra={\n                    \"memory_id\": str(request.memory_id),\n                    \"tenant_id\": request.tenant_id,\n                },\n            )\n\n    # Step 2 — provider call (skipped on cache hit).\n    if embedding is None:\n        embedding = await provider.embed(request.content)\n\n    # Step 3 — persist. Raises on non-2xx → nacks → redelivers.\n    # Per-tenant slot scoped to the PATCH roundtrip only, so a\n    # tenant-A storm can't park every storage-writer connection here\n    # while tenant B's lone PATCH queues behind. Provider call above\n    # stays unguarded — that's the expensive step and it doesn't\n    # touch the storage-writer pool.\n    async with per_tenant_storage_slot(request.tenant_id):\n        await update_memory_embedding(\n            storage,\n            memory_id=request.memory_id,\n            tenant_id=request.tenant_id,\n            embedding=embedding,\n        )\n\n    # Back-channel: announce successful embed so core-api can fire\n    # post-embed contradiction detection. Closes the documented\n    # ``handle_memory_enriched`` gap that silently dropped detection\n    # whenever enrichment landed before embedding (the only case under\n    # ``EMBED_ON_HOT_PATH=false``). Best-effort — a publish failure\n    # MUST NOT nack the upstream PATCH that already succeeded; the\n    # embedding is durable in storage either way.\n    try:\n        await publish_memory_embedded(\n            memory_id=request.memory_id,\n            tenant_id=request.tenant_id,\n            content=request.content,\n        )\n    except Exception:\n        logger.exception(\n            \"embedded back-channel publish failed; ack-continuing\",\n            extra={\n                \"memory_id\": str(request.memory_id),\n                \"tenant_id\": request.tenant_id,\n            },\n        )\n\n    logger.info(\n        \"embed-request processed\",\n        extra={\n            \"memory_id\": str(request.memory_id),\n            \"tenant_id\": request.tenant_id,\n            \"provider\": provider.provider_name,\n            \"model\": provider.model,\n        },\n    )\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Enrich-request consumer (CAURA-595)\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n# ORM column fields the worker writes directly. Stays in sync with the\n# corresponding ``Memory`` columns + the synchronous-path mapping in\n# ``core_api.services.memory_service``. Anything an ``EnrichmentResult``\n# field would write to but isn't here lands in ``metadata_patch`` below.\n_ENRICHMENT_ORM_FIELDS: frozenset[str] = frozenset(\n    {\n        \"memory_type\",\n        \"weight\",\n        \"title\",\n        \"status\",\n        \"ts_valid_start\",\n        \"ts_valid_end\",\n    }\n)\n\n# Enrichment fields that live in ``Memory.metadata`` JSONB. Synchronous\n# path (``memory_service.py``) writes them as ``metadata[\"summary\"]``,\n# ``metadata[\"tags\"]``, etc.; the worker mirrors that via the storage\n# layer's atomic ``metadata_patch`` JSONB merge.\n_ENRICHMENT_METADATA_FIELDS: frozenset[str] = frozenset(\n    {\n        \"summary\",\n        \"tags\",\n        \"contains_pii\",\n        \"pii_types\",\n        \"retrieval_hint\",\n        \"llm_ms\",\n    }\n)\n\n# ``EnrichmentResult`` fields the worker INTENTIONALLY does not route\n# to storage. Listed explicitly so the exhaustive-routing assert below\n# fails when a future field is added without a code site to handle it\n# — silent drops are the failure mode we're guarding against.\n#\n# ``atomic_facts``: the synchronous write path fans these out into\n# child memories; the async worker doesn't yet implement that — see\n# the ``logger.debug`` in ``handle_enrich_request`` that surfaces the\n# gap when an enrichment produces them.\n_ENRICHMENT_UNROUTED_FIELDS: frozenset[str] = frozenset({\"atomic_facts\"})\n\n# Metadata fields that ALWAYS overwrite (when not ``None`` and the\n# result came from a real LLM call — see the ``llm_ms > 0`` guard at\n# the call site) so a re-delivery / second-LLM-run can clear stale\n# state from an earlier write. JSONB ``||`` merge treats ``False`` /\n# ``\"\"`` / ``[]`` as ordinary values and overwrites keyed entries.\n#\n# * ``contains_pii`` / ``pii_types`` — non-deterministic LLM output;\n#   an earlier ``contains_pii=True`` must be clearable.\n# * ``retrieval_hint`` — the prompt explicitly instructs the LLM to\n#   return ``\"\"`` for content that's already query-aligned; without\n#   always-write a re-enrichment that drops the hint would leave\n#   metadata stale AND the embedding still prefix-augmented.\n# * ``tags`` — the prompt instructs the LLM to always populate 2-6\n#   tags. ``tags=[]`` from a real LLM run means \"no tags\" intentionally\n#   and must overwrite a prior non-empty list.\n# * ``summary`` — without the guard, a heuristic-fallback redelivery\n#   would write ``fake_enrich``'s ``summary=content[:200]`` over a\n#   prior quality LLM summary. The truncation is a non-empty string,\n#   so the ``value in (False, 0, \"\", [])`` skip-check below doesn't\n#   catch it. Pairing summary with the ``llm_ms > 0`` guard ensures\n#   only real-LLM summaries can overwrite (or clear, if the LLM\n#   returns ``\"\"``).\n_ENRICHMENT_ALWAYS_WRITE_METADATA: frozenset[str] = frozenset(\n    {\"contains_pii\", \"pii_types\", \"retrieval_hint\", \"summary\", \"tags\"}\n)\n\n# Defence-in-depth: a typo in the tuples above would silently drop in\n# the storage layer's ``hasattr(Memory, key)`` filter, *and* a future\n# ``EnrichmentResult`` field that no one wires to a routing tuple\n# would silently fall on the floor. Catch both at module import.\n_unrouted = (\n    set(EnrichmentResult.model_fields)\n    - _ENRICHMENT_ORM_FIELDS\n    - _ENRICHMENT_METADATA_FIELDS\n    - _ENRICHMENT_UNROUTED_FIELDS\n)\n# Raise rather than ``assert`` — ``python -O`` strips assertions, and\n# this guard's whole point is to surface routing-table drift on every\n# import in every environment. Matches\n# ``_assert_override_fields_match_schemas`` in ``memory_service.py``.\nif _unrouted:\n    raise RuntimeError(\n        f\"EnrichmentResult fields not routed to storage by handle_enrich_request: \"\n        f\"{sorted(_unrouted)} — add to one of _ENRICHMENT_ORM_FIELDS / \"\n        f\"_ENRICHMENT_METADATA_FIELDS / _ENRICHMENT_UNROUTED_FIELDS\"\n    )\ndel _unrouted\n\n\ndef _build_tenant_config(request: MemoryEnrichRequest) -> SimpleNamespace | None:\n    \"\"\"Reconstruct a duck-typed tenant_config from the event payload.\n\n    ``common.enrichment.service.enrich_memory`` only reads attributes\n    off ``tenant_config``; a ``SimpleNamespace`` matching that surface is\n    enough — no need to import ``ResolvedConfig``.\n\n    Returns ``None`` only when the payload genuinely carries no\n    tenant-specific config — neither a provider preference nor any API\n    keys. The early-return on ``enrichment_provider is None`` alone\n    would silently discard a tenant's keys, making the async path\n    behave differently from the sync path: sync sees\n    ``provider=None`` and defaults to ``\"openai\"`` while still using\n    the tenant's ``openai_api_key``; async would fall through to the\n    platform-tier provider or the heuristic. The check below mirrors\n    sync semantics — if any credential is present we build the\n    namespace with ``enrichment_provider=None`` and let\n    :func:`enrich_memory` apply its ``or ProviderName.OPENAI``\n    default.\n    \"\"\"\n    has_any_credentials = any(\n        (\n            request.openai_api_key,\n            request.anthropic_api_key,\n            request.openrouter_api_key,\n            request.gemini_api_key,\n        )\n    )\n    if request.enrichment_provider is None and not has_any_credentials:\n        return None\n\n    fb_provider = request.fallback_provider\n    fb_model = request.fallback_model\n\n    def resolve_fallback() -> tuple[str | None, str | None]:\n        return fb_provider, fb_model\n\n    return SimpleNamespace(\n        enrichment_provider=request.enrichment_provider,\n        enrichment_model=request.enrichment_model,\n        openai_api_key=request.openai_api_key,\n        anthropic_api_key=request.anthropic_api_key,\n        openrouter_api_key=request.openrouter_api_key,\n        gemini_api_key=request.gemini_api_key,\n        # Synthesised callable matches the\n        # ``ResolvedConfig.resolve_fallback()`` shape ``call_with_fallback``\n        # expects. The publisher already pre-resolved the tuple at\n        # publish time so the worker doesn't run the policy itself.\n        resolve_fallback=resolve_fallback,\n    )\n\n\ndef _build_patch(\n    result: EnrichmentResult,","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":360,"totalLines":625,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/consumer.py","time":{"start":1780728096224,"end":1780728096238}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08e5fcc45007da07016a23c1202300819199fcf948ab3468a0"}},"id":"prt_e9baa65ce001Ycbu2oG3W83fD4","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baa349f0019jejG5h4SaVZZ7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728096244,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_XCEFyIlvZgKFN27mHt098GRH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/app.py","offset":1,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/app.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"FastAPI application for core-worker.\n2: \n3: Consumer-only service — no business HTTP routes, just ``/healthz`` +\n4: ``/readyz`` so Cloud Run / k8s can probe liveness and readiness.\n5: \n6: Lifespan ordering:\n7: 1. ``configure_logging`` reads env BEFORE any module that emits log records.\n8: 2. ``init_platform_providers`` materialises BOTH platform-tier singletons:\n9:    the embedding provider from ``PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_*`` and the LLM\n10:    provider from ``PLATFORM_LLM_*``. Done eagerly so a bad config fails\n11:    the readiness probe instead of nacking every event. Both are needed:\n12:    ``handle_embed_request`` consults the embedding singleton;\n13:    ``handle_enrich_request`` falls through to the LLM singleton when the\n14:    request payload has no tenant-key for the resolved provider (CAURA-647\n15:    — pre-fix, the worker only inited embedding, so any payload that\n16:    resolved to ``ProviderName.OPENAI`` without a tenant openai key fell\n17:    straight through to FakeLLMProvider, silently corrupting the\n18:    re-enrichment path).\n19: 3. ``register_consumers`` wires ``handle_embed_request`` against\n20:    ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED``.\n21: 4. ``bus.start()`` spawns Pub/Sub pull loops (no-op for inprocess bus).\n22: \n23: Shutdown reverses: stop the bus (drains in-flight messages), close the\n24: shared httpx client, log.\n25: \"\"\"\n26: \n27: from __future__ import annotations\n28: \n29: import contextlib\n30: import logging\n31: from collections.abc import AsyncIterator\n32: \n33: from fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException\n34: \n35: from common.events.base import EventBus\n36: from common.events.factory import get_event_bus\n37: from common.events.lifecycle_handlers import (\n38:     register_consumers as register_lifecycle_consumers,\n39: )\n40: from common.llm import init_platform_providers\n41: from common.structlog_config import configure_logging\n42: from core_worker.clients.storage_client import close_storage_client, get_storage_client\n43: from core_worker.config import Settings\n44: from core_worker.consumer import configure as configure_consumer\n45: from core_worker.consumer import register_consumers\n46: from core_worker.lifecycle import make_storage_adapter as make_lifecycle_adapter\n47: \n48: settings = Settings()  # type: ignore[call-arg]\n49: \n50: # Configure logging before any imports emit log records.\n51: configure_logging(\n52:     settings.environment,\n53:     settings.log_level,\n54:     json_logs=settings.log_format_json,\n55:     log_file=settings.log_file or None,\n56: )\n57: \n58: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n59: \n60: _event_bus: EventBus | None = None\n61: \n62: \n63: async def _is_ready() -> bool:\n64:     \"\"\"Readiness check: bus singleton present + still healthy.\n65: \n66:     `bus.is_healthy` flips False on the Pub/Sub backend when any pull\n67:     loop has halted on a permanent error (subscription missing, SA\n68:     permission revoked) — without this check, a misconfigured pod\n69:     stays \"ready\" while silently dropping every inbound event.\n70:     \"\"\"\n71:     return _event_bus is not None and _event_bus.is_healthy\n72: \n73: \n74: @contextlib.asynccontextmanager\n75: async def lifespan(app: FastAPI) -> AsyncIterator[None]:\n76:     \"\"\"Application lifespan manager.\"\"\"\n77:     global _event_bus\n78: \n79:     logger.info(\"Starting core-worker\", extra={\"environment\": settings.environment})\n80: \n81:     # Eager platform-provider init: builds BOTH the embedding and LLM\n82:     # singletons from ``PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_*`` / ``PLATFORM_LLM_*``. The\n83:     # LLM half is what ``handle_enrich_request`` falls through to when\n84:     # a request payload's resolved provider has no tenant key — without\n85:     # it the enrichment path silently drops to ``FakeLLMProvider``\n86:     # (CAURA-647). A bad PLATFORM_* config fails the readiness probe\n87:     # rather than nacking every event.\n88:     init_platform_providers()\n89: \n90:     # Bind the consumer to its dependencies before subscribing — the\n91:     # subscribe must happen BEFORE bus.start() because the Pub/Sub\n92:     # backend spawns pull loops based on the current handler registry.\n93:     configure_consumer(get_storage_client)\n94:     register_consumers()\n95: \n96:     # CAURA-655: lifecycle archive consumers share the same Pub/Sub\n97:     # transport. Adapter wraps the worker's httpx storage client into\n98:     # the shape the shared handler expects.\n99:     register_lifecycle_consumers(make_lifecycle_adapter())\n100: \n101:     _event_bus = get_event_bus()\n102:     await _event_bus.start()\n103: \n104:     yield\n105: \n106:     logger.info(\"Shutting down core-worker\")\n107:     if _event_bus is not None:\n108:         await _event_bus.stop()\n109:         _event_bus = None\n110:     await close_storage_client()\n111: \n112: \n113: def create_app() -> FastAPI:\n114:     \"\"\"Create and configure the FastAPI application.\"\"\"\n115:     app = FastAPI(\n116:         title=\"MemClaw Core Worker\",\n117:         description=(\n118:             \"Async-embed event consumer.\\n\\n\"\n119:             \"Subscribes to ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED`` and PATCHes \"\n120:             \"computed embeddings back to core-storage-api. Exposes only \"\n121:             \"health endpoints.\"\n122:         ),\n123:         version=\"1.0.1\",\n124:         lifespan=lifespan,\n125:     )\n126: \n127:     @app.get(\"/healthz\")\n128:     async def healthz() -> dict[str, str]:\n129:         return {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n130: \n131:     @app.get(\"/readyz\")\n132:     async def readyz() -> dict[str, str]:\n133:         # Kubernetes and Cloud Run readiness probes gate on the HTTP\n134:         # status code — a 2xx body of ``{\"status\": \"not_ready\"}`` would\n135:         # leave the pod in rotation. Raise 503 so the load balancer\n136:         # actually drains a misconfigured / bus-halted pod.\n137:         if not await _is_ready():\n138:             raise HTTPException(status_code=503, detail=\"not_ready\")\n139:         return {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n140: \n141:     return app\n142: \n143: \n144: app = create_app()\n\n(End of file - total 144 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"FastAPI application for core-worker.\n\nConsumer-only service — no business HTTP routes, just ``/healthz`` +\n``/readyz`` so Cloud Run / k8s can probe liveness and readiness.\n\nLifespan ordering:\n1. ``configure_logging`` reads env BEFORE any module that emits log records.\n2. ``init_platform_providers`` materialises BOTH platform-tier singletons:\n   the embedding provider from ``PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_*`` and the LLM\n   provider from ``PLATFORM_LLM_*``. Done eagerly so a bad config fails\n   the readiness probe instead of nacking every event. Both are needed:\n   ``handle_embed_request`` consults the embedding singleton;\n   ``handle_enrich_request`` falls through to the LLM singleton when the\n   request payload has no tenant-key for the resolved provider (CAURA-647\n   — pre-fix, the worker only inited embedding, so any payload that\n   resolved to ``ProviderName.OPENAI`` without a tenant openai key fell\n   straight through to FakeLLMProvider, silently corrupting the\n   re-enrichment path).\n3. ``register_consumers`` wires ``handle_embed_request`` against\n   ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED``.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/app.py","text":"\"\"\"FastAPI application for core-worker.\n\nConsumer-only service — no business HTTP routes, just ``/healthz`` +\n``/readyz`` so Cloud Run / k8s can probe liveness and readiness.\n\nLifespan ordering:\n1. ``configure_logging`` reads env BEFORE any module that emits log records.\n2. ``init_platform_providers`` materialises BOTH platform-tier singletons:\n   the embedding provider from ``PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_*`` and the LLM\n   provider from ``PLATFORM_LLM_*``. Done eagerly so a bad config fails\n   the readiness probe instead of nacking every event. Both are needed:\n   ``handle_embed_request`` consults the embedding singleton;\n   ``handle_enrich_request`` falls through to the LLM singleton when the\n   request payload has no tenant-key for the resolved provider (CAURA-647\n   — pre-fix, the worker only inited embedding, so any payload that\n   resolved to ``ProviderName.OPENAI`` without a tenant openai key fell\n   straight through to FakeLLMProvider, silently corrupting the\n   re-enrichment path).\n3. ``register_consumers`` wires ``handle_embed_request`` against\n   ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED``.\n4. ``bus.start()`` spawns Pub/Sub pull loops (no-op for inprocess bus).\n\nShutdown reverses: stop the bus (drains in-flight messages), close the\nshared httpx client, log.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport contextlib\nimport logging\nfrom collections.abc import AsyncIterator\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException\n\nfrom common.events.base import EventBus\nfrom common.events.factory import get_event_bus\nfrom common.events.lifecycle_handlers import (\n    register_consumers as register_lifecycle_consumers,\n)\nfrom common.llm import init_platform_providers\nfrom common.structlog_config import configure_logging\nfrom core_worker.clients.storage_client import close_storage_client, get_storage_client\nfrom core_worker.config import Settings\nfrom core_worker.consumer import configure as configure_consumer\nfrom core_worker.consumer import register_consumers\nfrom core_worker.lifecycle import make_storage_adapter as make_lifecycle_adapter\n\nsettings = Settings()  # type: ignore[call-arg]\n\n# Configure logging before any imports emit log records.\nconfigure_logging(\n    settings.environment,\n    settings.log_level,\n    json_logs=settings.log_format_json,\n    log_file=settings.log_file or None,\n)\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n_event_bus: EventBus | None = None\n\n\nasync def _is_ready() -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Readiness check: bus singleton present + still healthy.\n\n    `bus.is_healthy` flips False on the Pub/Sub backend when any pull\n    loop has halted on a permanent error (subscription missing, SA\n    permission revoked) — without this check, a misconfigured pod\n    stays \"ready\" while silently dropping every inbound event.\n    \"\"\"\n    return _event_bus is not None and _event_bus.is_healthy\n\n\n@contextlib.asynccontextmanager\nasync def lifespan(app: FastAPI) -> AsyncIterator[None]:\n    \"\"\"Application lifespan manager.\"\"\"\n    global _event_bus\n\n    logger.info(\"Starting core-worker\", extra={\"environment\": settings.environment})\n\n    # Eager platform-provider init: builds BOTH the embedding and LLM\n    # singletons from ``PLATFORM_EMBEDDING_*`` / ``PLATFORM_LLM_*``. The\n    # LLM half is what ``handle_enrich_request`` falls through to when\n    # a request payload's resolved provider has no tenant key — without\n    # it the enrichment path silently drops to ``FakeLLMProvider``\n    # (CAURA-647). A bad PLATFORM_* config fails the readiness probe\n    # rather than nacking every event.\n    init_platform_providers()\n\n    # Bind the consumer to its dependencies before subscribing — the\n    # subscribe must happen BEFORE bus.start() because the Pub/Sub\n    # backend spawns pull loops based on the current handler registry.\n    configure_consumer(get_storage_client)\n    register_consumers()\n\n    # CAURA-655: lifecycle archive consumers share the same Pub/Sub\n    # transport. Adapter wraps the worker's httpx storage client into\n    # the shape the shared handler expects.\n    register_lifecycle_consumers(make_lifecycle_adapter())\n\n    _event_bus = get_event_bus()\n    await _event_bus.start()\n\n    yield\n\n    logger.info(\"Shutting down core-worker\")\n    if _event_bus is not None:\n        await _event_bus.stop()\n        _event_bus = None\n    await close_storage_client()\n\n\ndef create_app() -> FastAPI:\n    \"\"\"Create and configure the FastAPI application.\"\"\"\n    app = FastAPI(\n        title=\"MemClaw Core Worker\",\n        description=(\n            \"Async-embed event consumer.\\n\\n\"\n            \"Subscribes to ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED`` and PATCHes \"\n            \"computed embeddings back to core-storage-api. Exposes only \"\n            \"health endpoints.\"\n        ),\n        version=\"1.0.1\",\n        lifespan=lifespan,\n    )\n\n    @app.get(\"/healthz\")\n    async def healthz() -> dict[str, str]:\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n    @app.get(\"/readyz\")\n    async def readyz() -> dict[str, str]:\n        # Kubernetes and Cloud Run readiness probes gate on the HTTP\n        # status code — a 2xx body of ``{\"status\": \"not_ready\"}`` would\n        # leave the pod in rotation. Raise 503 so the load balancer\n        # actually drains a misconfigured / bus-halted pod.\n        if not await _is_ready():\n            raise HTTPException(status_code=503, detail=\"not_ready\")\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n    return app\n\n\napp = create_app()","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":144,"totalLines":144,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/app.py","time":{"start":1780728096234,"end":1780728096242}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08e5fcc45007da07016a23c12023108191bfa869b845b6dc42"}},"id":"prt_e9baa65e8001EBa149kRJVFjcL","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baa349f0019jejG5h4SaVZZ7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728096247,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_qSYPjbLYNIFHn2mscONsKUsQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_enriched.py","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_enriched.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Typed payload for the ``memclaw.memory.enriched`` topic (CAURA-595).\n2: \n3: Counterpart to :class:`~common.events.memory_enrich_request.MemoryEnrichRequest`:\n4: core-worker emits one of these *after* successfully PATCHing enrichment\n5: fields onto the memory row. core-api subscribes for downstream side\n6: effects — primarily a hint-driven re-embed when the LLM produced a\n7: ``retrieval_hint`` that would beat the raw-content embedding's\n8: recall.\n9: \n10: Carries the minimum the back-channel consumer needs: enough to reach the\n11: right row plus the hint (already validated/trimmed by\n12: ``_validate_enrichment``). The full ``EnrichmentResult`` is *not*\n13: shipped — it's already persisted, anyone who needs it can read storage.\n14: \n15: Empty / missing ``retrieval_hint`` is a signal that no re-embed is\n16: warranted (heuristic-fallback enrichments, content-already-query-aligned\n17: inputs).\n18: \n19: The envelope itself is :class:`common.events.base.Event`; this is just\n20: the shape of its ``payload`` dict.\n21: \"\"\"\n22: \n23: from __future__ import annotations\n24: \n25: from uuid import UUID\n26: \n27: from pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field\n28: \n29: \n30: class MemoryEnriched(BaseModel):\n31:     \"\"\"Announce a successful enrichment of a memory row.\"\"\"\n32: \n33:     # ``extra=\"ignore\"`` for the same rolling-deploy reason as\n34:     # ``MemoryEnrichRequest``: this is a cross-service consumer schema\n35:     # (core-api subscribes to what core-worker publishes). With\n36:     # ``forbid``, a worker-shipped-first additive field would fail\n37:     # validation in core-api during the deploy window and silently\n38:     # ack-drop every back-channel message until core-api updates. The\n39:     # publisher-side construction is the strict-validation boundary.\n40:     model_config = ConfigDict(frozen=True, extra=\"ignore\")\n41: \n42:     memory_id: UUID\n43:     tenant_id: str\n44:     # Carried so the back-channel consumer doesn't need a storage GET\n45:     # round trip just to dispatch contradiction detection. Same trade\n46:     # we made for ``MemoryEmbedRequest.content``.\n47:     content: str = Field(min_length=1)\n48:     # Empty string when the enricher produced no useful hint —\n49:     # back-channel consumers should short-circuit on falsy.\n50:     retrieval_hint: str = \"\"\n\n(End of file - total 50 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Typed payload for the ``memclaw.memory.enriched`` topic (CAURA-595).\n\nCounterpart to :class:`~common.events.memory_enrich_request.MemoryEnrichRequest`:\ncore-worker emits one of these *after* successfully PATCHing enrichment\nfields onto the memory row. core-api subscribes for downstream side\neffects — primarily a hint-driven re-embed when the LLM produced a\n``retrieval_hint`` that would beat the raw-content embedding's\nrecall.\n\nCarries the minimum the back-channel consumer needs: enough to reach the\nright row plus the hint (already validated/trimmed by\n``_validate_enrichment``). The full ``EnrichmentResult`` is *not*\nshipped — it's already persisted, anyone who needs it can read storage.\n\nEmpty / missing ``retrieval_hint`` is a signal that no re-embed is\nwarranted (heuristic-fallback enrichments, content-already-query-aligned\ninputs).\n\nThe envelope itself is :class:`common.events.base.Event`; this is just\nthe shape of its ``payload`` dict.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_enriched.py","text":"\"\"\"Typed payload for the ``memclaw.memory.enriched`` topic (CAURA-595).\n\nCounterpart to :class:`~common.events.memory_enrich_request.MemoryEnrichRequest`:\ncore-worker emits one of these *after* successfully PATCHing enrichment\nfields onto the memory row. core-api subscribes for downstream side\neffects — primarily a hint-driven re-embed when the LLM produced a\n``retrieval_hint`` that would beat the raw-content embedding's\nrecall.\n\nCarries the minimum the back-channel consumer needs: enough to reach the\nright row plus the hint (already validated/trimmed by\n``_validate_enrichment``). The full ``EnrichmentResult`` is *not*\nshipped — it's already persisted, anyone who needs it can read storage.\n\nEmpty / missing ``retrieval_hint`` is a signal that no re-embed is\nwarranted (heuristic-fallback enrichments, content-already-query-aligned\ninputs).\n\nThe envelope itself is :class:`common.events.base.Event`; this is just\nthe shape of its ``payload`` dict.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom uuid import UUID\n\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field\n\n\nclass MemoryEnriched(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Announce a successful enrichment of a memory row.\"\"\"\n\n    # ``extra=\"ignore\"`` for the same rolling-deploy reason as\n    # ``MemoryEnrichRequest``: this is a cross-service consumer schema\n    # (core-api subscribes to what core-worker publishes). With\n    # ``forbid``, a worker-shipped-first additive field would fail\n    # validation in core-api during the deploy window and silently\n    # ack-drop every back-channel message until core-api updates. The\n    # publisher-side construction is the strict-validation boundary.\n    model_config = ConfigDict(frozen=True, extra=\"ignore\")\n\n    memory_id: UUID\n    tenant_id: str\n    # Carried so the back-channel consumer doesn't need a storage GET\n    # round trip just to dispatch contradiction detection. Same trade\n    # we made for ``MemoryEmbedRequest.content``.\n    content: str = Field(min_length=1)\n    # Empty string when the enricher produced no useful hint —\n    # back-channel consumers should short-circuit on falsy.\n    retrieval_hint: str = \"\"","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":50,"totalLines":50,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_enriched.py","time":{"start":1780728096243,"end":1780728096246}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08e5fcc45007da07016a23c120231c819197e3595145bfc3ff"}},"id":"prt_e9baa65eb001vWa53dl9yVzxXp","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baa349f0019jejG5h4SaVZZ7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728096259,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_HQuZe4JJ7O3veqvW835pAgsP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_embedded_publisher.py","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_embedded_publisher.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Publish ``Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED`` events.\n2: \n3: Convenience wrapper for the worker so the post-PATCH publish doesn't\n4: re-build the ``Event`` envelope + ``MemoryEmbedded`` payload by hand.\n5: The helper validates the payload via Pydantic before publishing —\n6: schema drift surfaces here at publish time rather than on the\n7: consumer side.\n8: \n9: Mirrors :func:`common.events.memory_enriched_publisher.publish_memory_enriched`\n10: in shape; consumed by ``core-api``'s ``handle_memory_embedded`` to\n11: fire post-embed contradiction detection.\n12: \"\"\"\n13: \n14: from __future__ import annotations\n15: \n16: from uuid import UUID\n17: \n18: from common.events.base import Event\n19: from common.events.factory import get_event_bus\n20: from common.events.memory_embedded import MemoryEmbedded\n21: from common.events.topics import Topics\n22: \n23: \n24: async def publish_memory_embedded(\n25:     *,\n26:     memory_id: UUID,\n27:     content: str,\n28:     tenant_id: str,\n29: ) -> None:\n30:     \"\"\"Announce successful embedding of *memory_id*.\n31: \n32:     Fire-and-forget: ``bus.publish`` returns once the transport has\n33:     accepted the message. Caller (the worker's\n34:     ``handle_embed_request``) wraps in tracking so a transport error\n35:     on the back-channel doesn't nack the upstream PATCH that already\n36:     succeeded — the embedding is durable in storage either way, this\n37:     event is best-effort signalling.\n38:     \"\"\"\n39:     payload = MemoryEmbedded(\n40:         memory_id=memory_id,\n41:         tenant_id=tenant_id,\n42:         content=content,\n43:     )\n44:     event = Event(\n45:         event_type=Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED,\n46:         tenant_id=tenant_id,\n47:         payload=payload.model_dump(mode=\"json\"),\n48:     )\n49:     bus = get_event_bus()\n50:     await bus.publish(Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED, event)\n\n(End of file - total 50 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Publish ``Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED`` events.\n\nConvenience wrapper for the worker so the post-PATCH publish doesn't\nre-build the ``Event`` envelope + ``MemoryEmbedded`` payload by hand.\nThe helper validates the payload via Pydantic before publishing —\nschema drift surfaces here at publish time rather than on the\nconsumer side.\n\nMirrors :func:`common.events.memory_enriched_publisher.publish_memory_enriched`\nin shape; consumed by ``core-api``'s ``handle_memory_embedded`` to\nfire post-embed contradiction detection.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom uuid import UUID\n\nfrom common.events.base import Event\nfrom common.events.factory import get_event_bus\nfrom common.events.memory_embedded import MemoryEmbedded","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_embedded_publisher.py","text":"\"\"\"Publish ``Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED`` events.\n\nConvenience wrapper for the worker so the post-PATCH publish doesn't\nre-build the ``Event`` envelope + ``MemoryEmbedded`` payload by hand.\nThe helper validates the payload via Pydantic before publishing —\nschema drift surfaces here at publish time rather than on the\nconsumer side.\n\nMirrors :func:`common.events.memory_enriched_publisher.publish_memory_enriched`\nin shape; consumed by ``core-api``'s ``handle_memory_embedded`` to\nfire post-embed contradiction detection.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom uuid import UUID\n\nfrom common.events.base import Event\nfrom common.events.factory import get_event_bus\nfrom common.events.memory_embedded import MemoryEmbedded\nfrom common.events.topics import Topics\n\n\nasync def publish_memory_embedded(\n    *,\n    memory_id: UUID,\n    content: str,\n    tenant_id: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Announce successful embedding of *memory_id*.\n\n    Fire-and-forget: ``bus.publish`` returns once the transport has\n    accepted the message. Caller (the worker's\n    ``handle_embed_request``) wraps in tracking so a transport error\n    on the back-channel doesn't nack the upstream PATCH that already\n    succeeded — the embedding is durable in storage either way, this\n    event is best-effort signalling.\n    \"\"\"\n    payload = MemoryEmbedded(\n        memory_id=memory_id,\n        tenant_id=tenant_id,\n        content=content,\n    )\n    event = Event(\n        event_type=Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED,\n        tenant_id=tenant_id,\n        payload=payload.model_dump(mode=\"json\"),\n    )\n    bus = get_event_bus()\n    await bus.publish(Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED, event)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":50,"totalLines":50,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_embedded_publisher.py","time":{"start":1780728096255,"end":1780728096258}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08e5fcc45007da07016a23c12023248191ad309a2fbdc2cb39"}},"id":"prt_e9baa65fb001Gk7s6L3TSNSjmA","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baa349f0019jejG5h4SaVZZ7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728096277,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_pssOfylv1HrIhe2kgHe3Sigg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_enriched_publisher.py","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_enriched_publisher.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Publish ``Topics.Memory.ENRICHED`` events (CAURA-595).\n2: \n3: Convenience wrapper for the worker so the post-PATCH publish doesn't\n4: re-build the ``Event`` envelope + ``MemoryEnriched`` payload by hand.\n5: The helper validates the payload via Pydantic before publishing —\n6: schema drift surfaces here at publish time rather than on the\n7: consumer side.\n8: \n9: Mirrors :func:`common.events.memory_embed_publisher.publish_memory_embed_request`\n10: in shape; consumed by ``core-api`` once it registers a back-channel\n11: subscriber (also CAURA-595).\n12: \"\"\"\n13: \n14: from __future__ import annotations\n15: \n16: from uuid import UUID\n17: \n18: from common.events.base import Event\n19: from common.events.factory import get_event_bus\n20: from common.events.memory_enriched import MemoryEnriched\n21: from common.events.topics import Topics\n22: \n23: \n24: async def publish_memory_enriched(\n25:     *,\n26:     memory_id: UUID,\n27:     content: str,\n28:     tenant_id: str,\n29:     retrieval_hint: str = \"\",\n30: ) -> None:\n31:     \"\"\"Announce successful enrichment of *memory_id*.\n32: \n33:     Fire-and-forget: ``bus.publish`` returns once the transport has\n34:     accepted the message. Caller (the worker's\n35:     ``handle_enrich_request``) wraps in tracking so a transport error\n36:     on the back-channel doesn't nack the upstream PATCH that already\n37:     succeeded — the enrichment is durable in storage either way, this\n38:     event is best-effort signalling.\n39:     \"\"\"\n40:     payload = MemoryEnriched(\n41:         memory_id=memory_id,\n42:         tenant_id=tenant_id,\n43:         content=content,\n44:         retrieval_hint=retrieval_hint,\n45:     )\n46:     event = Event(\n47:         event_type=Topics.Memory.ENRICHED,\n48:         tenant_id=tenant_id,\n49:         payload=payload.model_dump(mode=\"json\"),\n50:     )\n51:     bus = get_event_bus()\n52:     await bus.publish(Topics.Memory.ENRICHED, event)\n\n(End of file - total 52 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Publish ``Topics.Memory.ENRICHED`` events (CAURA-595).\n\nConvenience wrapper for the worker so the post-PATCH publish doesn't\nre-build the ``Event`` envelope + ``MemoryEnriched`` payload by hand.\nThe helper validates the payload via Pydantic before publishing —\nschema drift surfaces here at publish time rather than on the\nconsumer side.\n\nMirrors :func:`common.events.memory_embed_publisher.publish_memory_embed_request`\nin shape; consumed by ``core-api`` once it registers a back-channel\nsubscriber (also CAURA-595).\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom uuid import UUID\n\nfrom common.events.base import Event\nfrom common.events.factory import get_event_bus\nfrom common.events.memory_enriched import MemoryEnriched","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_enriched_publisher.py","text":"\"\"\"Publish ``Topics.Memory.ENRICHED`` events (CAURA-595).\n\nConvenience wrapper for the worker so the post-PATCH publish doesn't\nre-build the ``Event`` envelope + ``MemoryEnriched`` payload by hand.\nThe helper validates the payload via Pydantic before publishing —\nschema drift surfaces here at publish time rather than on the\nconsumer side.\n\nMirrors :func:`common.events.memory_embed_publisher.publish_memory_embed_request`\nin shape; consumed by ``core-api`` once it registers a back-channel\nsubscriber (also CAURA-595).\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom uuid import UUID\n\nfrom common.events.base import Event\nfrom common.events.factory import get_event_bus\nfrom common.events.memory_enriched import MemoryEnriched\nfrom common.events.topics import Topics\n\n\nasync def publish_memory_enriched(\n    *,\n    memory_id: UUID,\n    content: str,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    retrieval_hint: str = \"\",\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Announce successful enrichment of *memory_id*.\n\n    Fire-and-forget: ``bus.publish`` returns once the transport has\n    accepted the message. Caller (the worker's\n    ``handle_enrich_request``) wraps in tracking so a transport error\n    on the back-channel doesn't nack the upstream PATCH that already\n    succeeded — the enrichment is durable in storage either way, this\n    event is best-effort signalling.\n    \"\"\"\n    payload = MemoryEnriched(\n        memory_id=memory_id,\n        tenant_id=tenant_id,\n        content=content,\n        retrieval_hint=retrieval_hint,\n    )\n    event = Event(\n        event_type=Topics.Memory.ENRICHED,\n        tenant_id=tenant_id,\n        payload=payload.model_dump(mode=\"json\"),\n    )\n    bus = get_event_bus()\n    await bus.publish(Topics.Memory.ENRICHED, event)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":52,"totalLines":52,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_enriched_publisher.py","time":{"start":1780728096273,"end":1780728096276}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08e5fcc45007da07016a23c120232c8191aa6b4ae1d337c6c0"}},"id":"prt_e9baa6600001L2MaZSNLf4V1nx","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baa349f0019jejG5h4SaVZZ7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728096292,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_8HEqggnwXlgFkwldUb9h5YSy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"def find_embedding_by_content_hash|def update_memory_embedding|def update_memory_enrichment|def get_storage_client|find_embedding_by_content_hash|update_memory_embedding|update_memory_enrichment","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker","include":"*.py"},"output":"Found 12 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/consumer.py:\n  Line 67:     find_embedding_by_content_hash,\n\n  Line 68:     update_memory_embedding,\n\n  Line 69:     update_memory_enrichment,\n\n  Line 147:         embedding = await find_embedding_by_content_hash(\n\n  Line 172:         await update_memory_embedding(\n\n  Line 548:         await update_memory_enrichment(\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-worker/src/core_worker/clients/storage_client.py:\n  Line 48: def get_storage_client() -> httpx.AsyncClient:\n\n  Line 128: async def find_embedding_by_content_hash(\n\n  Line 168: async def update_memory_embedding(\n\n  Line 454: async def update_memory_enrichment(\n\n  Line 463:     Mirrors :func:`update_memory_embedding` for the\n\n  Line 477:     Same 404/422 short-circuits as :func:`update_memory_embedding`.\n","metadata":{"matches":12,"truncated":false},"title":"def find_embedding_by_content_hash|def update_memory_embedding|def update_memory_enrichment|def get_storage_client|find_embedding_by_content_hash|update_memory_embedding|update_memory_enrichment","time":{"start":1780728096278,"end":1780728096291}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08e5fcc45007da07016a23c1202330819191959bd36725aba3"}},"id":"prt_e9baa6612001uR0ay3xxJYHnfr","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baa349f0019jejG5h4SaVZZ7"}}
