{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780728111908,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"id":"prt_e9baaa322001bdvEYcDDgJ3UE1","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"814e34449c1c0cd4511b93284e3947c86465093d","messageID":"msg_e9baa6841001Ctocor307bFP0E","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":60232,"input":8820,"output":466,"reasoning":258,"cache":{"write":0,"read":50688}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780728113343,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"id":"prt_e9baaa8bc001bvne9I1c7nnjfs","messageID":"msg_e9baaa426001o76uwc3IG1Cx97","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","snapshot":"28f207a342fb5ac19a1629e40ed4d343752a9a87","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1780728124662,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"id":"prt_e9baab5d00017jVcBQFHOJ7EJ3","messageID":"msg_e9baaa426001o76uwc3IG1Cx97","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","type":"text","text":"A notable correction emerged: MemClaw’s newer code documents hint-based re-embed as disabled in the write path, while enrichment still emits hints for metadata/back-channel consumers. I’m checking that path before drawing transfer conclusions.","time":{"start":1780728116688,"end":1780728124660},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d39ef22427eb546016a23c134a910819188cd52731caa4a57","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728124717,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_hjvOEI83uqfG2iCPE99F1Uz0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/consumer.py","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/consumer.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Pub/Sub consumer for core-api.\n2: \n3: Subscribes core-api to two back-channels published by core-worker\n4: after the async write path lands a memory row:\n5: \n6: * ``Topics.Memory.ENRICHED`` (CAURA-595) — fired after a successful\n7:   enrichment PATCH.\n8: * ``Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED`` (loadtest-7 fix) — fired after a\n9:   successful embedding PATCH.\n10: \n11: Both consumers run :func:`detect_contradictions_async`. Two events\n12: trigger the detector because either the embed or the enrich worker\n13: can land first, and the detector needs both fields available; whichever\n14: event arrives second sees the other side present and runs detection.\n15: The detector is idempotent under repeated calls on the same row, so\n16: the rare case where both events trigger detection back-to-back doesn't\n17: double-write contradiction rows.\n18: \n19: Atomic-fact fan-out (parent → child memories) is intentionally not\n20: handled here. The worker drops ``EnrichmentResult.atomic_facts``\n21: entirely (see ``_ENRICHMENT_UNROUTED_FIELDS`` in\n22: ``core-worker/src/core_worker/consumer.py``), so they never reach\n23: storage. Persisting them at the worker side and fanning out from a\n24: storage fetch is a separate piece of work.\n25: \"\"\"\n26: \n27: from __future__ import annotations\n28: \n29: import logging\n30: \n31: from pydantic import ValidationError\n32: \n33: from common.events.base import Event\n34: from common.events.factory import get_event_bus\n35: from common.events.memory_embedded import MemoryEmbedded\n36: from common.events.memory_enriched import MemoryEnriched\n37: from common.events.topics import Topics\n38: from core_api.clients.storage_client import get_storage_client\n39: from core_api.services.contradiction_detector import detect_contradictions_async\n40: \n41: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n42: \n43: \n44: async def handle_memory_enriched(event: Event) -> None:\n45:     \"\"\"Process one ``Topics.Memory.ENRICHED`` event.\n46: \n47:     Loads the memory row from storage (so we have the embedding +\n48:     fleet_id that the minimal payload doesn't carry) and dispatches to\n49:     ``detect_contradictions_async`` when the embedding has already\n50:     landed. Schema-drift / malformed payloads ack-drop with a loud\n51:     ``dropped=True`` log entry so a poison message can't loop the\n52:     subscription.\n53: \n54:     The detection coroutine is awaited inline rather than spawned via\n55:     ``track_task``: it owns its own ``try/except`` and never raises, so\n56:     the bus always acks regardless of detection outcome — but the await\n57:     delays the ack until detection completes, which prevents\n58:     redelivery from stacking concurrent detections on the same memory.\n59:     \"\"\"\n60:     try:\n61:         payload = MemoryEnriched(**event.payload)\n62:     except (ValidationError, TypeError):\n63:         # ``ValidationError`` covers shape drift (missing required\n64:         # fields, wrong types). ``TypeError`` covers ``event.payload``\n65:         # not being a mapping at all — ``**non_dict`` raises before\n66:         # Pydantic ever sees it. Both are poison-message conditions\n67:         # that re-raising would just nack-loop on; ack-drop loudly.\n68:         logger.exception(\n69:             \"dropping malformed memory-enriched payload\",\n70:             extra={\n71:                 \"event_type\": event.event_type,\n72:                 \"event_id\": str(event.event_id),\n73:                 \"dropped\": True,\n74:             },\n75:         )\n76:         return\n77: \n78:     sc = get_storage_client()\n79:     memory = await sc.get_memory(str(payload.memory_id))\n80:     if memory is None:\n81:         # Row was deleted between the worker's PATCH and our handler\n82:         # picking up the event. Common-enough race to ack-drop without\n83:         # noise; matches the worker's 404 handling.\n84:         logger.info(\n85:             \"memory-enriched: target row missing; ack-dropping\",\n86:             extra={\n87:                 \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n88:                 \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n89:             },\n90:         )\n91:         return\n92: \n93:     embedding = memory.get(\"embedding\")\n94:     if not embedding:\n95:         # Embed worker hasn't completed yet (or its PATCH 404'd).\n96:         # ``deferred_reason`` is structured so a Cloud Logging metric\n97:         # can scrape the count of skipped detections — without it,\n98:         # there's no production visibility into how often the race\n99:         # fires.\n100:         logger.info(\n101:             \"memory-enriched: embedding not yet present; deferring contradiction detection\",\n102:             extra={\n103:                 \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n104:                 \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n105:                 \"deferred_reason\": \"embedding_missing\",\n106:             },\n107:         )\n108:         return\n109: \n110:     fleet_id = memory.get(\"fleet_id\")\n111: \n112:     # Pass the already-fetched row through so the detector skips a\n113:     # redundant ``sc.get_memory`` (it still re-checks ``deleted_at``\n114:     # for the soft-delete-during-detection race).\n115:     await detect_contradictions_async(\n116:         payload.memory_id,\n117:         payload.tenant_id,\n118:         fleet_id,\n119:         payload.content,\n120:         embedding,\n121:         new_memory=memory,\n122:     )\n123: \n124:     logger.info(\n125:         \"memory-enriched processed\",\n126:         extra={\n127:             \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n128:             \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n129:             \"fleet_id\": fleet_id,\n130:             \"embedding_dim\": len(embedding),\n131:         },\n132:     )\n133: \n134: \n135: async def handle_memory_embedded(event: Event) -> None:\n136:     \"\"\"Process one ``Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED`` event.\n137: \n138:     Mirror of :func:`handle_memory_enriched` for the embed-finishes-\n139:     after-enrich ordering. Loads the memory row from storage (so we\n140:     have the embedding the minimal payload doesn't carry, plus\n141:     ``fleet_id``) and dispatches to :func:`detect_contradictions_async`\n142:     once the embedding has landed. Schema-drift / malformed payloads\n143:     ack-drop with a loud ``dropped=True`` log entry so a poison\n144:     message can't loop the subscription.\n145: \n146:     Like the enriched handler, the detection coroutine is awaited\n147:     inline rather than spawned via ``track_task``: it owns its own\n148:     ``try/except`` and never raises, so the bus always acks regardless\n149:     of detection outcome — but the await delays the ack until detection\n150:     completes, which prevents redelivery from stacking concurrent\n151:     detections on the same memory.\n152:     \"\"\"\n153:     try:\n154:         payload = MemoryEmbedded(**event.payload)\n155:     except (ValidationError, TypeError):\n156:         logger.exception(\n157:             \"dropping malformed memory-embedded payload\",\n158:             extra={\n159:                 \"event_type\": event.event_type,\n160:                 \"event_id\": str(event.event_id),\n161:                 \"dropped\": True,\n162:             },\n163:         )\n164:         return\n165: \n166:     sc = get_storage_client()\n167:     memory = await sc.get_memory(str(payload.memory_id))\n168:     if memory is None:\n169:         # Row was deleted between the worker's PATCH and our handler\n170:         # picking up the event. Common-enough race to ack-drop without\n171:         # noise; matches the worker's 404 handling.\n172:         logger.info(\n173:             \"memory-embedded: target row missing; ack-dropping\",\n174:             extra={\n175:                 \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n176:                 \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n177:             },\n178:         )\n179:         return\n180: \n181:     embedding = memory.get(\"embedding\")\n182:     if not embedding:\n183:         # Should not happen — the embed worker just PATCHed it before\n184:         # publishing — but guard against a soft-delete or column\n185:         # rewrite race rather than passing None into the detector.\n186:         logger.warning(\n187:             \"memory-embedded: embedding missing on read-back; ack-dropping\",\n188:             extra={\n189:                 \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n190:                 \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n191:             },\n192:         )\n193:         return\n194: \n195:     fleet_id = memory.get(\"fleet_id\")\n196: \n197:     await detect_contradictions_async(\n198:         payload.memory_id,\n199:         payload.tenant_id,\n200:         fleet_id,\n201:         payload.content,\n202:         embedding,\n203:         new_memory=memory,\n204:     )\n205: \n206:     logger.info(\n207:         \"memory-embedded processed\",\n208:         extra={\n209:             \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n210:             \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n211:             \"fleet_id\": fleet_id,\n212:             \"embedding_dim\": len(embedding),\n213:         },\n214:     )\n215: \n216: \n217: def register_consumers() -> None:\n218:     \"\"\"Wire the consumers into the event bus.\n219: \n220:     Must run before ``bus.start()`` — the Pub/Sub backend spawns its\n221:     pull loops in ``start()`` from the current handler registry, so a\n222:     late ``subscribe()`` would silently orphan the handler.\n223:     \"\"\"\n224:     bus = get_event_bus()\n225:     bus.subscribe(Topics.Memory.ENRICHED, handle_memory_enriched)\n226:     bus.subscribe(Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED, handle_memory_embedded)\n\n(End of file - total 226 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Pub/Sub consumer for core-api.\n\nSubscribes core-api to two back-channels published by core-worker\nafter the async write path lands a memory row:\n\n* ``Topics.Memory.ENRICHED`` (CAURA-595) — fired after a successful\n  enrichment PATCH.\n* ``Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED`` (loadtest-7 fix) — fired after a\n  successful embedding PATCH.\n\nBoth consumers run :func:`detect_contradictions_async`. Two events\ntrigger the detector because either the embed or the enrich worker\ncan land first, and the detector needs both fields available; whichever\nevent arrives second sees the other side present and runs detection.\nThe detector is idempotent under repeated calls on the same row, so\nthe rare case where both events trigger detection back-to-back doesn't\ndouble-write contradiction rows.\n\nAtomic-fact fan-out (parent → child memories) is intentionally not\nhandled here. The worker drops ``EnrichmentResult.atomic_facts``","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/consumer.py","text":"\"\"\"Pub/Sub consumer for core-api.\n\nSubscribes core-api to two back-channels published by core-worker\nafter the async write path lands a memory row:\n\n* ``Topics.Memory.ENRICHED`` (CAURA-595) — fired after a successful\n  enrichment PATCH.\n* ``Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED`` (loadtest-7 fix) — fired after a\n  successful embedding PATCH.\n\nBoth consumers run :func:`detect_contradictions_async`. Two events\ntrigger the detector because either the embed or the enrich worker\ncan land first, and the detector needs both fields available; whichever\nevent arrives second sees the other side present and runs detection.\nThe detector is idempotent under repeated calls on the same row, so\nthe rare case where both events trigger detection back-to-back doesn't\ndouble-write contradiction rows.\n\nAtomic-fact fan-out (parent → child memories) is intentionally not\nhandled here. The worker drops ``EnrichmentResult.atomic_facts``\nentirely (see ``_ENRICHMENT_UNROUTED_FIELDS`` in\n``core-worker/src/core_worker/consumer.py``), so they never reach\nstorage. Persisting them at the worker side and fanning out from a\nstorage fetch is a separate piece of work.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\n\nfrom pydantic import ValidationError\n\nfrom common.events.base import Event\nfrom common.events.factory import get_event_bus\nfrom common.events.memory_embedded import MemoryEmbedded\nfrom common.events.memory_enriched import MemoryEnriched\nfrom common.events.topics import Topics\nfrom core_api.clients.storage_client import get_storage_client\nfrom core_api.services.contradiction_detector import detect_contradictions_async\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nasync def handle_memory_enriched(event: Event) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Process one ``Topics.Memory.ENRICHED`` event.\n\n    Loads the memory row from storage (so we have the embedding +\n    fleet_id that the minimal payload doesn't carry) and dispatches to\n    ``detect_contradictions_async`` when the embedding has already\n    landed. Schema-drift / malformed payloads ack-drop with a loud\n    ``dropped=True`` log entry so a poison message can't loop the\n    subscription.\n\n    The detection coroutine is awaited inline rather than spawned via\n    ``track_task``: it owns its own ``try/except`` and never raises, so\n    the bus always acks regardless of detection outcome — but the await\n    delays the ack until detection completes, which prevents\n    redelivery from stacking concurrent detections on the same memory.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        payload = MemoryEnriched(**event.payload)\n    except (ValidationError, TypeError):\n        # ``ValidationError`` covers shape drift (missing required\n        # fields, wrong types). ``TypeError`` covers ``event.payload``\n        # not being a mapping at all — ``**non_dict`` raises before\n        # Pydantic ever sees it. Both are poison-message conditions\n        # that re-raising would just nack-loop on; ack-drop loudly.\n        logger.exception(\n            \"dropping malformed memory-enriched payload\",\n            extra={\n                \"event_type\": event.event_type,\n                \"event_id\": str(event.event_id),\n                \"dropped\": True,\n            },\n        )\n        return\n\n    sc = get_storage_client()\n    memory = await sc.get_memory(str(payload.memory_id))\n    if memory is None:\n        # Row was deleted between the worker's PATCH and our handler\n        # picking up the event. Common-enough race to ack-drop without\n        # noise; matches the worker's 404 handling.\n        logger.info(\n            \"memory-enriched: target row missing; ack-dropping\",\n            extra={\n                \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n                \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n            },\n        )\n        return\n\n    embedding = memory.get(\"embedding\")\n    if not embedding:\n        # Embed worker hasn't completed yet (or its PATCH 404'd).\n        # ``deferred_reason`` is structured so a Cloud Logging metric\n        # can scrape the count of skipped detections — without it,\n        # there's no production visibility into how often the race\n        # fires.\n        logger.info(\n            \"memory-enriched: embedding not yet present; deferring contradiction detection\",\n            extra={\n                \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n                \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n                \"deferred_reason\": \"embedding_missing\",\n            },\n        )\n        return\n\n    fleet_id = memory.get(\"fleet_id\")\n\n    # Pass the already-fetched row through so the detector skips a\n    # redundant ``sc.get_memory`` (it still re-checks ``deleted_at``\n    # for the soft-delete-during-detection race).\n    await detect_contradictions_async(\n        payload.memory_id,\n        payload.tenant_id,\n        fleet_id,\n        payload.content,\n        embedding,\n        new_memory=memory,\n    )\n\n    logger.info(\n        \"memory-enriched processed\",\n        extra={\n            \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n            \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n            \"fleet_id\": fleet_id,\n            \"embedding_dim\": len(embedding),\n        },\n    )\n\n\nasync def handle_memory_embedded(event: Event) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Process one ``Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED`` event.\n\n    Mirror of :func:`handle_memory_enriched` for the embed-finishes-\n    after-enrich ordering. Loads the memory row from storage (so we\n    have the embedding the minimal payload doesn't carry, plus\n    ``fleet_id``) and dispatches to :func:`detect_contradictions_async`\n    once the embedding has landed. Schema-drift / malformed payloads\n    ack-drop with a loud ``dropped=True`` log entry so a poison\n    message can't loop the subscription.\n\n    Like the enriched handler, the detection coroutine is awaited\n    inline rather than spawned via ``track_task``: it owns its own\n    ``try/except`` and never raises, so the bus always acks regardless\n    of detection outcome — but the await delays the ack until detection\n    completes, which prevents redelivery from stacking concurrent\n    detections on the same memory.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        payload = MemoryEmbedded(**event.payload)\n    except (ValidationError, TypeError):\n        logger.exception(\n            \"dropping malformed memory-embedded payload\",\n            extra={\n                \"event_type\": event.event_type,\n                \"event_id\": str(event.event_id),\n                \"dropped\": True,\n            },\n        )\n        return\n\n    sc = get_storage_client()\n    memory = await sc.get_memory(str(payload.memory_id))\n    if memory is None:\n        # Row was deleted between the worker's PATCH and our handler\n        # picking up the event. Common-enough race to ack-drop without\n        # noise; matches the worker's 404 handling.\n        logger.info(\n            \"memory-embedded: target row missing; ack-dropping\",\n            extra={\n                \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n                \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n            },\n        )\n        return\n\n    embedding = memory.get(\"embedding\")\n    if not embedding:\n        # Should not happen — the embed worker just PATCHed it before\n        # publishing — but guard against a soft-delete or column\n        # rewrite race rather than passing None into the detector.\n        logger.warning(\n            \"memory-embedded: embedding missing on read-back; ack-dropping\",\n            extra={\n                \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n                \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n            },\n        )\n        return\n\n    fleet_id = memory.get(\"fleet_id\")\n\n    await detect_contradictions_async(\n        payload.memory_id,\n        payload.tenant_id,\n        fleet_id,\n        payload.content,\n        embedding,\n        new_memory=memory,\n    )\n\n    logger.info(\n        \"memory-embedded processed\",\n        extra={\n            \"memory_id\": str(payload.memory_id),\n            \"tenant_id\": payload.tenant_id,\n            \"fleet_id\": fleet_id,\n            \"embedding_dim\": len(embedding),\n        },\n    )\n\n\ndef register_consumers() -> None:\n    \"\"\"Wire the consumers into the event bus.\n\n    Must run before ``bus.start()`` — the Pub/Sub backend spawns its\n    pull loops in ``start()`` from the current handler registry, so a\n    late ``subscribe()`` would silently orphan the handler.\n    \"\"\"\n    bus = get_event_bus()\n    bus.subscribe(Topics.Memory.ENRICHED, handle_memory_enriched)\n    bus.subscribe(Topics.Memory.EMBEDDED, handle_memory_embedded)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":226,"totalLines":226,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/consumer.py","time":{"start":1780728124692,"end":1780728124715}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d39ef22427eb546016a23c13c9b9c819182197b2756b7f5fa"}},"id":"prt_e9baad4f5001PpyKUhT5YEOJ4L","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baaa426001o76uwc3IG1Cx97"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728124729,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_cpZqivu83pgh7TQvD9ieNXbn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","offset":1544,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1544: async def _schedule_embed_or_reembed(\n1545:     memory_id: UUID,\n1546:     content: str,\n1547:     tenant_id: str,\n1548:     *,\n1549:     content_hash: str | None = None,\n1550: ) -> None:\n1551:     \"\"\"Backfill the embedding for a memory persisted with ``embedding=NULL``.\n1552: \n1553:     Inline mode (OSS, no worker fleet): in-process retry via\n1554:     :func:`_reembed_memory`.\n1555:     Deferred mode (SaaS): publish ``EMBED_REQUESTED``; ``core-worker``\n1556:     PATCHes the row. ``content_hash`` is used by the worker to short-\n1557:     circuit the provider call when the same content was already\n1558:     embedded for this tenant — pass it whenever the caller has it in\n1559:     scope.\n1560:     \"\"\"\n1561:     if settings.inline_embedding:\n1562:         await _reembed_memory(memory_id, content, tenant_id)\n1563:     else:\n1564:         await publish_memory_embed_request(\n1565:             memory_id=memory_id,\n1566:             content=content,\n1567:             tenant_id=tenant_id,\n1568:             content_hash=content_hash,\n1569:         )\n1570: \n1571: \n1572: # Columns the agent may set explicitly on ``MemoryCreate`` /\n1573: # ``BulkMemoryItem`` that the enricher would otherwise overwrite. Used\n1574: # below to compute ``agent_provided_fields`` from\n1575: # ``Pydantic.model_fields_set`` for the worker's PATCH gate.\n1576: _ENRICHMENT_AGENT_OVERRIDE_FIELDS: frozenset[str] = frozenset(\n1577:     {\n1578:         \"memory_type\",\n1579:         \"weight\",\n1580:         \"status\",\n1581:         \"ts_valid_start\",\n1582:         \"ts_valid_end\",\n1583:     }\n1584: )\n1585: \n1586: \n1587: def _assert_override_fields_match_schemas() -> None:\n1588:     \"\"\"Catch typos / schema drift at import time.\n1589: \n1590:     The override-skip gate is the only thing protecting agent-provided\n1591:     values from being silently downgraded by the worker on every\n1592:     redelivery (``EnrichmentResult``'s Pydantic defaults survive\n1593:     ``model_dump(exclude_none=True)``). A misspelled name in the\n1594:     frozenset above would be invisible — the gate would simply never\n1595:     match, and data corruption would only surface as user complaints\n1596:     days later.\n1597:     \"\"\"\n1598:     from core_api.schemas import BulkMemoryItem, MemoryCreate\n1599: \n1600:     for cls in (MemoryCreate, BulkMemoryItem):\n1601:         missing = _ENRICHMENT_AGENT_OVERRIDE_FIELDS - set(cls.model_fields)\n1602:         if missing:\n1603:             raise RuntimeError(\n1604:                 f\"_ENRICHMENT_AGENT_OVERRIDE_FIELDS references fields \"\n1605:                 f\"missing from {cls.__name__}: {sorted(missing)}\"\n1606:             )\n1607: \n1608: \n1609: _assert_override_fields_match_schemas()\n1610: \n1611: \n1612: def _agent_provided_enrichment_fields(\n1613:     data: object,\n1614: ) -> list[str] | None:\n1615:     \"\"\"Snapshot which enrichment columns the agent set explicitly.\n1616: \n1617:     Reads ``Pydantic.BaseModel.model_fields_set`` if available — it\n1618:     contains exactly the fields the request body had a value for, before\n1619:     Pydantic applied defaults. The worker uses the result as the\n1620:     ``agent_provided_fields`` PATCH-skip list so a redelivery (or a\n1621:     slow worker run) can't downgrade an agent-provided ``weight=0.9``\n1622:     back to the schema default.\n1623: \n1624:     Returns ``None`` (= \"trust enrichment for everything\") when\n1625:     ``data`` doesn't expose ``model_fields_set`` — keeps the helper\n1626:     safe against synthetic test inputs.\n1627:     \"\"\"\n1628:     fields_set = getattr(data, \"model_fields_set\", None)\n1629:     if not fields_set:\n1630:         return None\n1631:     overlap = sorted(_ENRICHMENT_AGENT_OVERRIDE_FIELDS & fields_set)\n1632:     return overlap or None\n1633: \n1634: \n1635: async def _schedule_enrich_or_inline(\n1636:     memory_id: UUID,\n1637:     content: str,\n1638:     tenant_id: str,\n1639:     fleet_id: str | None,\n1640:     agent_id: str,\n1641:     tenant_config: object,\n1642:     *,\n1643:     agent_provided_fields: list[str] | None = None,\n1644:     reference_datetime: datetime | None = None,\n1645: ) -> None:\n1646:     \"\"\"Enrichment counterpart of :func:`_schedule_embed_or_reembed`.\n1647: \n1648:     Inline mode (OSS / pre-CAURA-595 default): run enrichment as an\n1649:     in-process background task in core-api via\n1650:     :func:`_enrich_memory_background`.\n1651:     Deferred mode (CAURA-595 SaaS): publish ``ENRICH_REQUESTED``;\n1652:     ``core-worker`` consumes the event, runs the LLM, and PATCHes the\n1653:     enrichment fields back. The worker also emits ``ENRICHED`` after\n1654:     the PATCH lands.\n1655: \n1656:     ``agent_provided_fields`` is forwarded so the worker doesn't\n1657:     overwrite anything the agent set explicitly at write time —\n1658:     critical because ``EnrichmentResult``'s Pydantic defaults survive\n1659:     ``model_dump(exclude_none=True)`` and would otherwise downgrade\n1660:     those columns on every redelivery.\n1661:     \"\"\"\n1662:     if settings.inline_enrichment:\n1663:         # NOTE: ``agent_provided_fields`` and ``reference_datetime``\n1664:         # are intentionally NOT forwarded to ``_enrich_memory_background``.\n1665:         # The inline path pre-dates these concepts and uses an\n1666:         # equivalent gate by reading the row's current value vs the\n1667:         # schema default (``if mem.get(\"memory_type\") == \"fact\" and\n1668:         # enrichment.memory_type:`` etc., see the body of\n1669:         # ``_enrich_memory_background``). When the agent set\n1670:         # ``memory_type=\"rule\"`` the column already reads ``\"rule\"``\n1671:         # not ``\"fact\"``, and the inline gate skips.\n1672:         #\n1673:         # The two paths converge on the same agent-wins outcome via\n1674:         # different mechanisms; unifying them on\n1675:         # ``agent_provided_fields`` is a reasonable cleanup but out of\n1676:         # scope for CAURA-595 — there's no observable behavioural\n1677:         # delta between the gates today.\n1678:         await _enrich_memory_background(memory_id, content, tenant_id, fleet_id, agent_id)\n1679:     else:\n1680:         await publish_memory_enrich_request(\n1681:             memory_id=memory_id,\n1682:             content=content,\n1683:             tenant_id=tenant_id,\n1684:             tenant_config=tenant_config,\n1685:             reference_datetime=reference_datetime,\n1686:             agent_provided_fields=agent_provided_fields,\n1687:         )\n1688: \n1689: \n1690: async def _reembed_memory(\n1691:     memory_id: UUID,\n1692:     content: str,\n1693:     tenant_id: str,\n1694:     *,\n1695:     is_failure_fallback: bool = False,\n1696: ) -> None:\n1697:     \"\"\"Background task: (optionally wait,) retry embedding, patch the row,\n1698:     then run contradiction detection.\n1699: \n1700:     The initial sleep is skipped by default — the common caller is the\n1701:     deliberate hot-path offload, where waiting 30s would blow the\n1702:     sub-2s freshness SLA. Callers that ARE retrying a just-failed\n1703:     provider call (e.g. batched re-embed falling back to per-item)\n1704:     must pass ``is_failure_fallback=True`` to get the backoff, otherwise\n1705:     N serial retries land on the already-failing provider with zero\n1706:     delay — thundering herd.\n1707:     \"\"\"\n1708:     from core_api.constants import EMBEDDING_REEMBED_DELAY_S\n1709:     from core_api.services.organization_settings import resolve_config\n1710: \n1711:     if settings.inline_embedding or is_failure_fallback:\n1712:         # Two paths land here: pre-offload legacy behaviour (inline mode,\n1713:         # this coroutine only runs on provider failure) and CAURA-594\n1714:         # batch-fallback (deferred mode but the batch just failed). Both\n1715:         # want the backoff.\n1716:         await asyncio.sleep(EMBEDDING_REEMBED_DELAY_S)\n1717:     try:\n1718:         tenant_config = await resolve_config(None, tenant_id)\n1719:     except Exception:\n1720:         logger.warning(\"Failed to resolve tenant config for re-embed (tenant=%s)\", tenant_id, exc_info=True)\n1721:         tenant_config = None\n1722: \n1723:     embedding = None\n1724:     for attempt in range(1, _REEMBED_MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n1725:         embedding = await get_embedding(content, tenant_config=tenant_config)\n1726:         if embedding is not None:\n1727:             break\n1728:         delay = _REEMBED_BACKOFF_BASE_S * attempt\n1729:         logger.warning(\n1730:             \"Re-embed attempt %d/%d failed for memory %s, retrying in %ds\",\n1731:             attempt,\n1732:             _REEMBED_MAX_RETRIES,\n1733:             memory_id,\n1734:             delay,\n1735:         )\n1736:         await asyncio.sleep(delay)\n1737:     if embedding is None:\n1738:         logger.error(\n1739:             \"Background re-embed exhausted all %d retries for memory %s\",\n1740:             _REEMBED_MAX_RETRIES,\n1741:             memory_id,\n1742:         )\n1743:         return\n1744: \n1745:     try:\n1746:         sc = get_storage_client()\n1747:         mem = await sc.get_memory(str(memory_id))\n1748:         if mem is None or mem.get(\"deleted_at\") is not None:\n1749:             return\n1750:         # Race guard: _enrich_memory_background may have already written a\n1751:         # hint-enhanced embedding for this row. Respect it (higher retrieval\n1752:         # quality than our raw-content embedding) and just fire contradiction\n1753:         # detection on the existing value instead of overwriting.\n1754:         #\n1755:         # Mode-agnostic: the race exists even under ``deployment_mode=\n1756:         # \"inline\"`` — in fast write mode with enrichment enabled, a\n1757:         # hot-path embed failure causes ScheduleBackgroundTasks to\n1758:         # queue BOTH _reembed and _enrich_memory_background, so enrich\n1759:         # can beat us to the row regardless of the deploy mode.\n1760:         if mem.get(\"embedding\") is not None:\n1761:             from core_api.services.contradiction_detector import detect_contradictions_async\n1762: \n1763:             track_task(\n1764:                 tracked_task(\n1765:                     detect_contradictions_async(\n1766:                         memory_id,\n1767:                         tenant_id,\n1768:                         mem.get(\"fleet_id\"),\n1769:                         content,\n1770:                         mem.get(\"embedding\"),\n1771:                     ),\n1772:                     \"contradiction_detection_post_reembed\",\n1773:                     memory_id,\n1774:                     tenant_id,\n1775:                 )\n1776:             )\n1777:             return\n1778:         await sc.update_embedding(str(memory_id), embedding)\n1779:         logger.info(\"Background re-embed succeeded for memory %s\", memory_id)\n1780:     except (TimeoutError, ValueError, RuntimeError, OpenAIError, GoogleAPIError):\n1781:         logger.exception(\"Background re-embed error for memory %s\", memory_id)\n1782:         return\n1783: \n\n(Showing lines 1544-1783 of 3230. Use offset=1784 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"async def _schedule_embed_or_reembed(\n    memory_id: UUID,\n    content: str,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    *,\n    content_hash: str | None = None,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Backfill the embedding for a memory persisted with ``embedding=NULL``.\n\n    Inline mode (OSS, no worker fleet): in-process retry via\n    :func:`_reembed_memory`.\n    Deferred mode (SaaS): publish ``EMBED_REQUESTED``; ``core-worker``\n    PATCHes the row. ``content_hash`` is used by the worker to short-\n    circuit the provider call when the same content was already\n    embedded for this tenant — pass it whenever the caller has it in\n    scope.\n    \"\"\"\n    if settings.inline_embedding:\n        await _reembed_memory(memory_id, content, tenant_id)\n    else:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","text":"async def _schedule_embed_or_reembed(\n    memory_id: UUID,\n    content: str,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    *,\n    content_hash: str | None = None,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Backfill the embedding for a memory persisted with ``embedding=NULL``.\n\n    Inline mode (OSS, no worker fleet): in-process retry via\n    :func:`_reembed_memory`.\n    Deferred mode (SaaS): publish ``EMBED_REQUESTED``; ``core-worker``\n    PATCHes the row. ``content_hash`` is used by the worker to short-\n    circuit the provider call when the same content was already\n    embedded for this tenant — pass it whenever the caller has it in\n    scope.\n    \"\"\"\n    if settings.inline_embedding:\n        await _reembed_memory(memory_id, content, tenant_id)\n    else:\n        await publish_memory_embed_request(\n            memory_id=memory_id,\n            content=content,\n            tenant_id=tenant_id,\n            content_hash=content_hash,\n        )\n\n\n# Columns the agent may set explicitly on ``MemoryCreate`` /\n# ``BulkMemoryItem`` that the enricher would otherwise overwrite. Used\n# below to compute ``agent_provided_fields`` from\n# ``Pydantic.model_fields_set`` for the worker's PATCH gate.\n_ENRICHMENT_AGENT_OVERRIDE_FIELDS: frozenset[str] = frozenset(\n    {\n        \"memory_type\",\n        \"weight\",\n        \"status\",\n        \"ts_valid_start\",\n        \"ts_valid_end\",\n    }\n)\n\n\ndef _assert_override_fields_match_schemas() -> None:\n    \"\"\"Catch typos / schema drift at import time.\n\n    The override-skip gate is the only thing protecting agent-provided\n    values from being silently downgraded by the worker on every\n    redelivery (``EnrichmentResult``'s Pydantic defaults survive\n    ``model_dump(exclude_none=True)``). A misspelled name in the\n    frozenset above would be invisible — the gate would simply never\n    match, and data corruption would only surface as user complaints\n    days later.\n    \"\"\"\n    from core_api.schemas import BulkMemoryItem, MemoryCreate\n\n    for cls in (MemoryCreate, BulkMemoryItem):\n        missing = _ENRICHMENT_AGENT_OVERRIDE_FIELDS - set(cls.model_fields)\n        if missing:\n            raise RuntimeError(\n                f\"_ENRICHMENT_AGENT_OVERRIDE_FIELDS references fields \"\n                f\"missing from {cls.__name__}: {sorted(missing)}\"\n            )\n\n\n_assert_override_fields_match_schemas()\n\n\ndef _agent_provided_enrichment_fields(\n    data: object,\n) -> list[str] | None:\n    \"\"\"Snapshot which enrichment columns the agent set explicitly.\n\n    Reads ``Pydantic.BaseModel.model_fields_set`` if available — it\n    contains exactly the fields the request body had a value for, before\n    Pydantic applied defaults. The worker uses the result as the\n    ``agent_provided_fields`` PATCH-skip list so a redelivery (or a\n    slow worker run) can't downgrade an agent-provided ``weight=0.9``\n    back to the schema default.\n\n    Returns ``None`` (= \"trust enrichment for everything\") when\n    ``data`` doesn't expose ``model_fields_set`` — keeps the helper\n    safe against synthetic test inputs.\n    \"\"\"\n    fields_set = getattr(data, \"model_fields_set\", None)\n    if not fields_set:\n        return None\n    overlap = sorted(_ENRICHMENT_AGENT_OVERRIDE_FIELDS & fields_set)\n    return overlap or None\n\n\nasync def _schedule_enrich_or_inline(\n    memory_id: UUID,\n    content: str,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    fleet_id: str | None,\n    agent_id: str,\n    tenant_config: object,\n    *,\n    agent_provided_fields: list[str] | None = None,\n    reference_datetime: datetime | None = None,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Enrichment counterpart of :func:`_schedule_embed_or_reembed`.\n\n    Inline mode (OSS / pre-CAURA-595 default): run enrichment as an\n    in-process background task in core-api via\n    :func:`_enrich_memory_background`.\n    Deferred mode (CAURA-595 SaaS): publish ``ENRICH_REQUESTED``;\n    ``core-worker`` consumes the event, runs the LLM, and PATCHes the\n    enrichment fields back. The worker also emits ``ENRICHED`` after\n    the PATCH lands.\n\n    ``agent_provided_fields`` is forwarded so the worker doesn't\n    overwrite anything the agent set explicitly at write time —\n    critical because ``EnrichmentResult``'s Pydantic defaults survive\n    ``model_dump(exclude_none=True)`` and would otherwise downgrade\n    those columns on every redelivery.\n    \"\"\"\n    if settings.inline_enrichment:\n        # NOTE: ``agent_provided_fields`` and ``reference_datetime``\n        # are intentionally NOT forwarded to ``_enrich_memory_background``.\n        # The inline path pre-dates these concepts and uses an\n        # equivalent gate by reading the row's current value vs the\n        # schema default (``if mem.get(\"memory_type\") == \"fact\" and\n        # enrichment.memory_type:`` etc., see the body of\n        # ``_enrich_memory_background``). When the agent set\n        # ``memory_type=\"rule\"`` the column already reads ``\"rule\"``\n        # not ``\"fact\"``, and the inline gate skips.\n        #\n        # The two paths converge on the same agent-wins outcome via\n        # different mechanisms; unifying them on\n        # ``agent_provided_fields`` is a reasonable cleanup but out of\n        # scope for CAURA-595 — there's no observable behavioural\n        # delta between the gates today.\n        await _enrich_memory_background(memory_id, content, tenant_id, fleet_id, agent_id)\n    else:\n        await publish_memory_enrich_request(\n            memory_id=memory_id,\n            content=content,\n            tenant_id=tenant_id,\n            tenant_config=tenant_config,\n            reference_datetime=reference_datetime,\n            agent_provided_fields=agent_provided_fields,\n        )\n\n\nasync def _reembed_memory(\n    memory_id: UUID,\n    content: str,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    *,\n    is_failure_fallback: bool = False,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Background task: (optionally wait,) retry embedding, patch the row,\n    then run contradiction detection.\n\n    The initial sleep is skipped by default — the common caller is the\n    deliberate hot-path offload, where waiting 30s would blow the\n    sub-2s freshness SLA. Callers that ARE retrying a just-failed\n    provider call (e.g. batched re-embed falling back to per-item)\n    must pass ``is_failure_fallback=True`` to get the backoff, otherwise\n    N serial retries land on the already-failing provider with zero\n    delay — thundering herd.\n    \"\"\"\n    from core_api.constants import EMBEDDING_REEMBED_DELAY_S\n    from core_api.services.organization_settings import resolve_config\n\n    if settings.inline_embedding or is_failure_fallback:\n        # Two paths land here: pre-offload legacy behaviour (inline mode,\n        # this coroutine only runs on provider failure) and CAURA-594\n        # batch-fallback (deferred mode but the batch just failed). Both\n        # want the backoff.\n        await asyncio.sleep(EMBEDDING_REEMBED_DELAY_S)\n    try:\n        tenant_config = await resolve_config(None, tenant_id)\n    except Exception:\n        logger.warning(\"Failed to resolve tenant config for re-embed (tenant=%s)\", tenant_id, exc_info=True)\n        tenant_config = None\n\n    embedding = None\n    for attempt in range(1, _REEMBED_MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n        embedding = await get_embedding(content, tenant_config=tenant_config)\n        if embedding is not None:\n            break\n        delay = _REEMBED_BACKOFF_BASE_S * attempt\n        logger.warning(\n            \"Re-embed attempt %d/%d failed for memory %s, retrying in %ds\",\n            attempt,\n            _REEMBED_MAX_RETRIES,\n            memory_id,\n            delay,\n        )\n        await asyncio.sleep(delay)\n    if embedding is None:\n        logger.error(\n            \"Background re-embed exhausted all %d retries for memory %s\",\n            _REEMBED_MAX_RETRIES,\n            memory_id,\n        )\n        return\n\n    try:\n        sc = get_storage_client()\n        mem = await sc.get_memory(str(memory_id))\n        if mem is None or mem.get(\"deleted_at\") is not None:\n            return\n        # Race guard: _enrich_memory_background may have already written a\n        # hint-enhanced embedding for this row. Respect it (higher retrieval\n        # quality than our raw-content embedding) and just fire contradiction\n        # detection on the existing value instead of overwriting.\n        #\n        # Mode-agnostic: the race exists even under ``deployment_mode=\n        # \"inline\"`` — in fast write mode with enrichment enabled, a\n        # hot-path embed failure causes ScheduleBackgroundTasks to\n        # queue BOTH _reembed and _enrich_memory_background, so enrich\n        # can beat us to the row regardless of the deploy mode.\n        if mem.get(\"embedding\") is not None:\n            from core_api.services.contradiction_detector import detect_contradictions_async\n\n            track_task(\n                tracked_task(\n                    detect_contradictions_async(\n                        memory_id,\n                        tenant_id,\n                        mem.get(\"fleet_id\"),\n                        content,\n                        mem.get(\"embedding\"),\n                    ),\n                    \"contradiction_detection_post_reembed\",\n                    memory_id,\n                    tenant_id,\n                )\n            )\n            return\n        await sc.update_embedding(str(memory_id), embedding)\n        logger.info(\"Background re-embed succeeded for memory %s\", memory_id)\n    except (TimeoutError, ValueError, RuntimeError, OpenAIError, GoogleAPIError):\n        logger.exception(\"Background re-embed error for memory %s\", memory_id)\n        return\n","lineStart":1544,"lineEnd":1783,"totalLines":3230,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","time":{"start":1780728124707,"end":1780728124727}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d39ef22427eb546016a23c13c9bc0819194517dccea36dc94"}},"id":"prt_e9baad521001x2qu64oZVO2qvM","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baaa426001o76uwc3IG1Cx97"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728124729,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7FZVxD4dmphHZkUsJT2m14wW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","offset":85,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n85: # env-level configuration, since that caused prior silent divergence between\n86: # deployments and the default code path.\n87: _USE_PIPELINE_WRITE = True\n88: _USE_PIPELINE_SEARCH = True\n89: \n90: \n91: def _content_hash(tenant_id: str, fleet_id: str | None, content: str) -> str:\n92:     return hashlib.sha256(f\"{tenant_id}:{fleet_id or ''}:{content}\".encode()).hexdigest()\n93: \n94: \n95: def _auto_chunk_request_id() -> str:\n96:     \"\"\"Mint a per-row attempt id for in-process bulk-insert callers\n97:     (auto-chunk, atomic-facts) that have no ``X-Bulk-Attempt-Id`` from\n98:     a client (CAURA-602). The ``auto-chunk:`` prefix keeps these rows\n99:     visually distinguishable in the partial unique index from\n100:     real client-side bulk attempts (``f\"{X-Bulk-Attempt-Id}:{idx}\"``).\n101:     \"\"\"\n102:     return f\"auto-chunk:{uuid4()}\"\n103: \n104: \n105: async def _find_semantic_duplicate(\n106:     db: AsyncSession,\n107:     tenant_id: str,\n108:     fleet_id: str | None,\n109:     embedding: list[float],\n110:     exclude_id: UUID | None = None,\n111:     visibility: str | None = None,\n112:     min_similarity: float | None = None,\n113: ) -> dict | None:\n114:     \"\"\"Find a near-duplicate memory via cosine similarity.\n115: \n116:     Returns the closest match above the threshold (or ``None``). The\n117:     returned dict carries a ``similarity`` field — added in A1 #16 so\n118:     two-tier callers can dispatch by score.\n119: \n120:     ``min_similarity`` defaults to ``SEMANTIC_DEDUP_THRESHOLD`` (0.95)\n121:     via the storage layer for back-compat. A1 #16's\n122:     ``CheckSemanticDuplicate`` pipeline step passes\n123:     ``SEMANTIC_DEDUP_JUDGE_THRESHOLD`` to surface the judge band.\n124:     \"\"\"\n125:     sc = get_storage_client()\n126:     payload: dict = {\n127:         \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n128:         \"fleet_id\": fleet_id,\n129:         \"embedding\": embedding,\n130:         \"exclude_id\": str(exclude_id) if exclude_id else None,\n131:         \"visibility\": visibility,\n132:     }\n133:     if min_similarity is not None:\n134:         payload[\"min_similarity\"] = min_similarity\n135:     return await sc.find_semantic_duplicate(payload)\n136: \n137: \n138: def _dict_to_memory_out(\n139:     mem: dict,\n140:     entity_links: list[EntityLinkOut] | None = None,\n141:     similarity: float | None = None,\n142:     contradictions: list[ContradictionInfo] | None = None,\n143: ) -> MemoryOut:\n144:     \"\"\"Convert a storage-client dict to MemoryOut.\"\"\"\n145:     # Explicit None-check: ``{}`` is falsy, so ``or`` would fall\n146:     # through to the legacy ``\"metadata\"`` key whenever the column\n147:     # is an intentional empty dict, masking the stored value as\n148:     # ``None`` in the API response.\n149:     raw_meta = mem.get(\"metadata_\")\n150:     metadata = raw_meta if raw_meta is not None else mem.get(\"metadata\")\n151:     return MemoryOut(\n152:         id=mem.get(\"id\"),\n153:         tenant_id=mem.get(\"tenant_id\"),\n154:         fleet_id=mem.get(\"fleet_id\"),\n155:         agent_id=mem.get(\"agent_id\"),\n156:         memory_type=mem.get(\"memory_type\"),\n157:         title=mem.get(\"title\"),\n158:         content=mem.get(\"content\"),\n159:         weight=mem.get(\"weight\"),\n160:         source_uri=mem.get(\"source_uri\"),\n161:         run_id=mem.get(\"run_id\"),\n162:         metadata=metadata,\n163:         created_at=mem.get(\"created_at\"),\n164:         expires_at=mem.get(\"expires_at\"),\n165:         entity_links=entity_links or [],\n166:         similarity=similarity,\n167:         subject_entity_id=mem.get(\"subject_entity_id\"),\n168:         predicate=mem.get(\"predicate\"),\n169:         object_value=mem.get(\"object_value\"),\n170:         ts_valid_start=mem.get(\"ts_valid_start\"),\n171:         ts_valid_end=mem.get(\"ts_valid_end\"),\n172:         status=mem.get(\"status\"),\n173:         visibility=mem.get(\"visibility\"),\n174:         recall_count=mem.get(\"recall_count\"),\n175:         last_recalled_at=mem.get(\"last_recalled_at\"),\n176:         supersedes_id=mem.get(\"supersedes_id\"),\n177:         superseded_by=contradictions if contradictions else None,\n178:     )\n179: \n180: \n181: def _mem_attr(memory, key: str, default=None):\n182:     \"\"\"Get a field from either an ORM Memory object or a dict.\"\"\"\n183:     if isinstance(memory, dict):\n184:         return memory.get(key, default)\n185:     return getattr(memory, key, default)\n186: \n187: \n188: def _memory_to_out(\n189:     memory,\n190:     entity_links: list[EntityLinkOut] | None = None,\n191:     similarity: float | None = None,\n192:     contradictions: list[ContradictionInfo] | None = None,\n193: ) -> MemoryOut:\n194:     # See ``_dict_to_memory_out`` for the falsy-``{}`` trap.\n195:     if isinstance(memory, dict):\n196:         raw_meta = memory.get(\"metadata_\")\n197:         metadata = raw_meta if raw_meta is not None else memory.get(\"metadata\")\n198:     else:\n199:         metadata = _mem_attr(memory, \"metadata_\")\n200:     return MemoryOut(\n201:         id=_mem_attr(memory, \"id\"),\n202:         tenant_id=_mem_attr(memory, \"tenant_id\"),\n203:         fleet_id=_mem_attr(memory, \"fleet_id\"),\n204:         agent_id=_mem_attr(memory, \"agent_id\"),\n\n(Showing lines 85-204 of 3230. Use offset=205 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# env-level configuration, since that caused prior silent divergence between\n# deployments and the default code path.\n_USE_PIPELINE_WRITE = True\n_USE_PIPELINE_SEARCH = True\n\n\ndef _content_hash(tenant_id: str, fleet_id: str | None, content: str) -> str:\n    return hashlib.sha256(f\"{tenant_id}:{fleet_id or ''}:{content}\".encode()).hexdigest()\n\n\ndef _auto_chunk_request_id() -> str:\n    \"\"\"Mint a per-row attempt id for in-process bulk-insert callers\n    (auto-chunk, atomic-facts) that have no ``X-Bulk-Attempt-Id`` from\n    a client (CAURA-602). The ``auto-chunk:`` prefix keeps these rows\n    visually distinguishable in the partial unique index from\n    real client-side bulk attempts (``f\"{X-Bulk-Attempt-Id}:{idx}\"``).\n    \"\"\"\n    return f\"auto-chunk:{uuid4()}\"\n\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","text":"# env-level configuration, since that caused prior silent divergence between\n# deployments and the default code path.\n_USE_PIPELINE_WRITE = True\n_USE_PIPELINE_SEARCH = True\n\n\ndef _content_hash(tenant_id: str, fleet_id: str | None, content: str) -> str:\n    return hashlib.sha256(f\"{tenant_id}:{fleet_id or ''}:{content}\".encode()).hexdigest()\n\n\ndef _auto_chunk_request_id() -> str:\n    \"\"\"Mint a per-row attempt id for in-process bulk-insert callers\n    (auto-chunk, atomic-facts) that have no ``X-Bulk-Attempt-Id`` from\n    a client (CAURA-602). The ``auto-chunk:`` prefix keeps these rows\n    visually distinguishable in the partial unique index from\n    real client-side bulk attempts (``f\"{X-Bulk-Attempt-Id}:{idx}\"``).\n    \"\"\"\n    return f\"auto-chunk:{uuid4()}\"\n\n\nasync def _find_semantic_duplicate(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    fleet_id: str | None,\n    embedding: list[float],\n    exclude_id: UUID | None = None,\n    visibility: str | None = None,\n    min_similarity: float | None = None,\n) -> dict | None:\n    \"\"\"Find a near-duplicate memory via cosine similarity.\n\n    Returns the closest match above the threshold (or ``None``). The\n    returned dict carries a ``similarity`` field — added in A1 #16 so\n    two-tier callers can dispatch by score.\n\n    ``min_similarity`` defaults to ``SEMANTIC_DEDUP_THRESHOLD`` (0.95)\n    via the storage layer for back-compat. A1 #16's\n    ``CheckSemanticDuplicate`` pipeline step passes\n    ``SEMANTIC_DEDUP_JUDGE_THRESHOLD`` to surface the judge band.\n    \"\"\"\n    sc = get_storage_client()\n    payload: dict = {\n        \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n        \"fleet_id\": fleet_id,\n        \"embedding\": embedding,\n        \"exclude_id\": str(exclude_id) if exclude_id else None,\n        \"visibility\": visibility,\n    }\n    if min_similarity is not None:\n        payload[\"min_similarity\"] = min_similarity\n    return await sc.find_semantic_duplicate(payload)\n\n\ndef _dict_to_memory_out(\n    mem: dict,\n    entity_links: list[EntityLinkOut] | None = None,\n    similarity: float | None = None,\n    contradictions: list[ContradictionInfo] | None = None,\n) -> MemoryOut:\n    \"\"\"Convert a storage-client dict to MemoryOut.\"\"\"\n    # Explicit None-check: ``{}`` is falsy, so ``or`` would fall\n    # through to the legacy ``\"metadata\"`` key whenever the column\n    # is an intentional empty dict, masking the stored value as\n    # ``None`` in the API response.\n    raw_meta = mem.get(\"metadata_\")\n    metadata = raw_meta if raw_meta is not None else mem.get(\"metadata\")\n    return MemoryOut(\n        id=mem.get(\"id\"),\n        tenant_id=mem.get(\"tenant_id\"),\n        fleet_id=mem.get(\"fleet_id\"),\n        agent_id=mem.get(\"agent_id\"),\n        memory_type=mem.get(\"memory_type\"),\n        title=mem.get(\"title\"),\n        content=mem.get(\"content\"),\n        weight=mem.get(\"weight\"),\n        source_uri=mem.get(\"source_uri\"),\n        run_id=mem.get(\"run_id\"),\n        metadata=metadata,\n        created_at=mem.get(\"created_at\"),\n        expires_at=mem.get(\"expires_at\"),\n        entity_links=entity_links or [],\n        similarity=similarity,\n        subject_entity_id=mem.get(\"subject_entity_id\"),\n        predicate=mem.get(\"predicate\"),\n        object_value=mem.get(\"object_value\"),\n        ts_valid_start=mem.get(\"ts_valid_start\"),\n        ts_valid_end=mem.get(\"ts_valid_end\"),\n        status=mem.get(\"status\"),\n        visibility=mem.get(\"visibility\"),\n        recall_count=mem.get(\"recall_count\"),\n        last_recalled_at=mem.get(\"last_recalled_at\"),\n        supersedes_id=mem.get(\"supersedes_id\"),\n        superseded_by=contradictions if contradictions else None,\n    )\n\n\ndef _mem_attr(memory, key: str, default=None):\n    \"\"\"Get a field from either an ORM Memory object or a dict.\"\"\"\n    if isinstance(memory, dict):\n        return memory.get(key, default)\n    return getattr(memory, key, default)\n\n\ndef _memory_to_out(\n    memory,\n    entity_links: list[EntityLinkOut] | None = None,\n    similarity: float | None = None,\n    contradictions: list[ContradictionInfo] | None = None,\n) -> MemoryOut:\n    # See ``_dict_to_memory_out`` for the falsy-``{}`` trap.\n    if isinstance(memory, dict):\n        raw_meta = memory.get(\"metadata_\")\n        metadata = raw_meta if raw_meta is not None else memory.get(\"metadata\")\n    else:\n        metadata = _mem_attr(memory, \"metadata_\")\n    return MemoryOut(\n        id=_mem_attr(memory, \"id\"),\n        tenant_id=_mem_attr(memory, \"tenant_id\"),\n        fleet_id=_mem_attr(memory, \"fleet_id\"),\n        agent_id=_mem_attr(memory, \"agent_id\"),","lineStart":85,"lineEnd":204,"totalLines":3230,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","time":{"start":1780728124702,"end":1780728124728}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d39ef22427eb546016a23c13c9bb4819185e11f44fab69969"}},"id":"prt_e9baad5150019BJIN9agLUi4k1","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baaa426001o76uwc3IG1Cx97"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728124730,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_i74JamTA3asssOEqkgLvAZ0u","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","offset":2030,"limit":100},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n2030: \n2031:     if enrichment is None:\n2032:         return\n2033: \n2034:     try:\n2035:         sc = get_storage_client()\n2036:         mem = await sc.get_memory(str(memory_id))\n2037:         if mem is None or mem.get(\"deleted_at\") is not None:\n2038:             return\n2039: \n2040:         # Build update patch\n2041:         patch: dict = {}\n2042:         if mem.get(\"memory_type\") == \"fact\" and enrichment.memory_type:\n2043:             patch[\"memory_type\"] = enrichment.memory_type\n2044:         if mem.get(\"weight\") == 0.5 and enrichment.weight is not None:\n2045:             patch[\"weight\"] = enrichment.weight\n2046:         if enrichment.title:\n2047:             patch[\"title\"] = enrichment.title\n2048: \n2049:         # See ``_dict_to_memory_out`` for the falsy-``{}`` trap.\n2050:         raw_meta = mem.get(\"metadata_\")\n2051:         existing = raw_meta if raw_meta is not None else mem.get(\"metadata\")\n2052:         meta = dict(existing) if existing is not None else {}\n2053:         if enrichment.summary:\n2054:             meta[\"summary\"] = enrichment.summary\n2055:         if enrichment.tags:\n2056:             meta[\"tags\"] = enrichment.tags\n2057:         if enrichment.llm_ms:\n2058:             meta[\"llm_ms\"] = enrichment.llm_ms\n2059:         if enrichment.contains_pii:\n2060:             meta[\"contains_pii\"] = True\n2061:             if enrichment.pii_types:\n2062:                 meta[\"pii_types\"] = enrichment.pii_types\n2063:         if enrichment.retrieval_hint:\n2064:             # Persisted for debugging / auditability only; no longer used\n2065:             # to shape the embedding (see CAURA-222).\n2066:             meta[\"retrieval_hint\"] = enrichment.retrieval_hint\n2067:         # Temporal resolution\n2068:         if mem.get(\"ts_valid_start\") is None and enrichment.ts_valid_start:\n2069:             patch[\"ts_valid_start\"] = enrichment.ts_valid_start\n2070:         if mem.get(\"ts_valid_end\") is None and enrichment.ts_valid_end:\n2071:             patch[\"ts_valid_end\"] = enrichment.ts_valid_end\n2072:         # Status: only upgrade from default \"active\"\n2073:         if mem.get(\"status\") == \"active\" and enrichment.status:\n2074:             patch[\"status\"] = enrichment.status\n2075: \n2076:         meta.pop(\"enrichment_pending\", None)\n2077:         patch[\"metadata_\"] = meta\n2078: \n2079:         # Apply patch via storage client -- use update_memory_status for status\n2080:         # and a general patch for other fields\n2081:         if patch:\n2082:             # The storage API update_memory_status handles status changes;\n2083:             # for other fields we need to build the right call\n2084:             status_val = patch.pop(\"status\", None)\n2085:             if patch:\n2086:                 # Use a generic memory patch (metadata, type, weight, etc.)\n2087:                 # Fall back to update via scored-search patch endpoint\n2088:                 await sc._patch(f\"/memories/{memory_id}\", patch)\n2089:             if status_val:\n2090:                 await sc.update_memory_status(str(memory_id), status_val)\n2091: \n2092:         memory_type = patch.get(\"memory_type\") or mem.get(\"memory_type\")\n2093: \n2094:         # Hint-based re-embed removed (CAURA-222): the hot path embeds raw\n2095:         # ``content`` and the search side embeds raw query, so the stored\n2096:         # vector is already on the correct surface by the time enrichment\n2097:         # finishes. Re-embedding ``content`` here would just produce an\n2098:         # identical vector — wasted provider call and DB write. F3 Phase 3\n2099:         # also removed the SaaS-mode contradiction-coverage branch that\n2100:         # used to live here; deferred-mode contradiction detection is now\n2101:         # fully owned by the worker consumers (handle_memory_embedded /\n2102:         # handle_memory_enriched), and OSS-mode contradiction fires\n2103:         # through the inline write pipeline before this function runs.\n2104: \n2105:         # Atomic-fact fan-out: if the enricher detected 2+ independent claims in\n2106:         # this turn, create a child memory for each so queries targeting a\n2107:         # specific fact retrieve it directly. Children embed raw\n2108:         # ``fact_content`` (not hint-prefixed) to keep the same write/query\n2109:         # surface as the search side — see CAURA-222. Failures here are\n2110:         # non-fatal to the parent.\n2111:         atomic_facts = getattr(enrichment, \"atomic_facts\", None) or []\n2112:         if len(atomic_facts) >= 1:\n2113:             parent_ts_start = mem.get(\"ts_valid_start\")\n2114:             parent_visibility = mem.get(\"visibility\") or \"scope_team\"\n2115:             parent_weight = patch.get(\"weight\") or mem.get(\"weight\") or 0.5\n2116:             fanout_created = 0\n2117:             for fact in atomic_facts:\n2118:                 fact_content = fact.content\n2119:                 try:\n2120:                     child_embedding = await get_embedding(fact_content, tenant_config=tenant_config)\n2121:                 except (TimeoutError, ValueError, RuntimeError, OpenAIError, GoogleAPIError):\n2122:                     logger.warning(\n2123:                         \"atomic-fact embed failed for memory %s (skipping this fact)\",\n2124:                         memory_id,\n2125:                         exc_info=True,\n2126:                     )\n2127:                     continue\n2128:                 if child_embedding is None:\n2129:                     continue\n\n(Showing lines 2030-2129 of 3230. Use offset=2130 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n    if enrichment is None:\n        return\n\n    try:\n        sc = get_storage_client()\n        mem = await sc.get_memory(str(memory_id))\n        if mem is None or mem.get(\"deleted_at\") is not None:\n            return\n\n        # Build update patch\n        patch: dict = {}\n        if mem.get(\"memory_type\") == \"fact\" and enrichment.memory_type:\n            patch[\"memory_type\"] = enrichment.memory_type\n        if mem.get(\"weight\") == 0.5 and enrichment.weight is not None:\n            patch[\"weight\"] = enrichment.weight\n        if enrichment.title:\n            patch[\"title\"] = enrichment.title\n\n        # See ``_dict_to_memory_out`` for the falsy-``{}`` trap.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","text":"\n    if enrichment is None:\n        return\n\n    try:\n        sc = get_storage_client()\n        mem = await sc.get_memory(str(memory_id))\n        if mem is None or mem.get(\"deleted_at\") is not None:\n            return\n\n        # Build update patch\n        patch: dict = {}\n        if mem.get(\"memory_type\") == \"fact\" and enrichment.memory_type:\n            patch[\"memory_type\"] = enrichment.memory_type\n        if mem.get(\"weight\") == 0.5 and enrichment.weight is not None:\n            patch[\"weight\"] = enrichment.weight\n        if enrichment.title:\n            patch[\"title\"] = enrichment.title\n\n        # See ``_dict_to_memory_out`` for the falsy-``{}`` trap.\n        raw_meta = mem.get(\"metadata_\")\n        existing = raw_meta if raw_meta is not None else mem.get(\"metadata\")\n        meta = dict(existing) if existing is not None else {}\n        if enrichment.summary:\n            meta[\"summary\"] = enrichment.summary\n        if enrichment.tags:\n            meta[\"tags\"] = enrichment.tags\n        if enrichment.llm_ms:\n            meta[\"llm_ms\"] = enrichment.llm_ms\n        if enrichment.contains_pii:\n            meta[\"contains_pii\"] = True\n            if enrichment.pii_types:\n                meta[\"pii_types\"] = enrichment.pii_types\n        if enrichment.retrieval_hint:\n            # Persisted for debugging / auditability only; no longer used\n            # to shape the embedding (see CAURA-222).\n            meta[\"retrieval_hint\"] = enrichment.retrieval_hint\n        # Temporal resolution\n        if mem.get(\"ts_valid_start\") is None and enrichment.ts_valid_start:\n            patch[\"ts_valid_start\"] = enrichment.ts_valid_start\n        if mem.get(\"ts_valid_end\") is None and enrichment.ts_valid_end:\n            patch[\"ts_valid_end\"] = enrichment.ts_valid_end\n        # Status: only upgrade from default \"active\"\n        if mem.get(\"status\") == \"active\" and enrichment.status:\n            patch[\"status\"] = enrichment.status\n\n        meta.pop(\"enrichment_pending\", None)\n        patch[\"metadata_\"] = meta\n\n        # Apply patch via storage client -- use update_memory_status for status\n        # and a general patch for other fields\n        if patch:\n            # The storage API update_memory_status handles status changes;\n            # for other fields we need to build the right call\n            status_val = patch.pop(\"status\", None)\n            if patch:\n                # Use a generic memory patch (metadata, type, weight, etc.)\n                # Fall back to update via scored-search patch endpoint\n                await sc._patch(f\"/memories/{memory_id}\", patch)\n            if status_val:\n                await sc.update_memory_status(str(memory_id), status_val)\n\n        memory_type = patch.get(\"memory_type\") or mem.get(\"memory_type\")\n\n        # Hint-based re-embed removed (CAURA-222): the hot path embeds raw\n        # ``content`` and the search side embeds raw query, so the stored\n        # vector is already on the correct surface by the time enrichment\n        # finishes. Re-embedding ``content`` here would just produce an\n        # identical vector — wasted provider call and DB write. F3 Phase 3\n        # also removed the SaaS-mode contradiction-coverage branch that\n        # used to live here; deferred-mode contradiction detection is now\n        # fully owned by the worker consumers (handle_memory_embedded /\n        # handle_memory_enriched), and OSS-mode contradiction fires\n        # through the inline write pipeline before this function runs.\n\n        # Atomic-fact fan-out: if the enricher detected 2+ independent claims in\n        # this turn, create a child memory for each so queries targeting a\n        # specific fact retrieve it directly. Children embed raw\n        # ``fact_content`` (not hint-prefixed) to keep the same write/query\n        # surface as the search side — see CAURA-222. Failures here are\n        # non-fatal to the parent.\n        atomic_facts = getattr(enrichment, \"atomic_facts\", None) or []\n        if len(atomic_facts) >= 1:\n            parent_ts_start = mem.get(\"ts_valid_start\")\n            parent_visibility = mem.get(\"visibility\") or \"scope_team\"\n            parent_weight = patch.get(\"weight\") or mem.get(\"weight\") or 0.5\n            fanout_created = 0\n            for fact in atomic_facts:\n                fact_content = fact.content\n                try:\n                    child_embedding = await get_embedding(fact_content, tenant_config=tenant_config)\n                except (TimeoutError, ValueError, RuntimeError, OpenAIError, GoogleAPIError):\n                    logger.warning(\n                        \"atomic-fact embed failed for memory %s (skipping this fact)\",\n                        memory_id,\n                        exc_info=True,\n                    )\n                    continue\n                if child_embedding is None:\n                    continue","lineStart":2030,"lineEnd":2129,"totalLines":3230,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","time":{"start":1780728124709,"end":1780728124729}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d39ef22427eb546016a23c13c9bc881918bc3896aecde526c"}},"id":"prt_e9baad523001uIlFzGMVDZ8R8u","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baaa426001o76uwc3IG1Cx97"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728124740,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_TGl5kBfqjeObVdDmknMlIVJu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/pipeline/steps/write/parallel_embed_enrich.py","offset":1,"limit":190},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/pipeline/steps/write/parallel_embed_enrich.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Concurrent embedding + LLM enrichment via asyncio.gather.\n2: \n3: Deferral is now ``write_mode``-aware (restores the original CAURA-229\n4: contract that the CAURA-524 step-consolidation + CAURA-595 PR-C global-\n5: flag pattern inadvertently flattened):\n6: \n7: * ``write_mode == \"strong\"`` → embed and enrich **always inline**,\n8:   regardless of ``settings.deployment_mode``. Strong callers\n9:   explicitly opted into \"thorough write before commit\"; the\n10:   per-deploy mode targets fast-mode latency, not strong. Running\n11:   inline here is what gives strong its meaningful guarantees —\n12:   ``CheckSemanticDuplicate`` runs against a real embedding (so the\n13:   409-on-near-duplicate contract holds), and the agent reads its own\n14:   enriched ``title`` / ``memory_type`` / ``weight`` / ``status`` /\n15:   ``ts_valid_*`` back in the response.\n16: * ``write_mode == \"fast\"`` → LLM enrichment **always deferred**\n17:   (matches CAURA-229's \"fast = no LLM on the request path\"\n18:   intent). Embedding follows ``settings.inline_embedding`` so OSS\n19:   local stays inline ~200ms while SaaS prod defers to ``core-worker``\n20:   for the sub-2s p99 visibility SLA.\n21: * Any other ``write_mode`` value (and the ``None`` case the\n22:   enrichment-only sub-pipeline hits during extract-only / auto-chunk)\n23:   reads both helpers — preserves today's behaviour for those\n24:   branches.\n25: \n26: Behind both deferred paths: ``ScheduleBackgroundTasks`` publishes\n27: ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED`` / ``Topics.Memory.ENRICH_REQUESTED``\n28: so ``core-worker`` runs the provider call and PATCHes the row back.\n29: Hint-based re-embed is DISABLED (CAURA-222): writes used to embed\n30: ``compose_embedding_text(content, retrieval_hint)`` while queries embed\n31: raw text, producing a write/query surface asymmetry that capped recall\n32: across dedup, entity-lookup, and search ranking. Until a symmetric\n33: reintroduction lands, both the hot-path here and the background\n34: re-embed in ``_enrich_memory_background`` embed raw ``content``.\n35: \"\"\"\n36: \n37: from __future__ import annotations\n38: \n39: import asyncio\n40: import logging\n41: import time\n42: from collections.abc import Awaitable\n43: from typing import Any\n44: \n45: from fastapi import HTTPException\n46: \n47: from common.embedding import get_embedding\n48: from core_api.config import settings\n49: from core_api.pipeline.context import PipelineContext\n50: from core_api.pipeline.step import StepResult\n51: \n52: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n53: \n54: \n55: async def _timed(awaitable: Awaitable[Any], timings: dict, key: str) -> Any:\n56:     \"\"\"Await ``awaitable`` and record its wall-clock duration into ``timings[key]``.\n57: \n58:     Used to separate embed and enrich latencies even though ``asyncio.gather``\n59:     runs them concurrently — without this, a slow LLM enrichment masks the\n60:     embedding's own latency in the gather wall-clock. The pre-/post-await\n61:     `perf_counter` samples each task's own time, so values are additive but\n62:     not exclusive (they overlap when gather runs both).\n63:     \"\"\"\n64:     t0 = time.perf_counter()\n65:     try:\n66:         return await awaitable\n67:     finally:\n68:         timings[key] = round((time.perf_counter() - t0) * 1000)\n69: \n70: \n71: class ParallelEmbedEnrich:\n72:     @property\n73:     def name(self) -> str:\n74:         return \"parallel_embed_enrich\"\n75: \n76:     async def execute(self, ctx: PipelineContext) -> StepResult | None:\n77:         data = ctx.data[\"input\"]\n78:         tenant_config = ctx.tenant_config\n79:         cached_embedding = ctx.data.get(\"cached_embedding\")\n80:         ch = ctx.data.get(\"content_hash\")\n81:         resolved_write_mode = ctx.data.get(\"resolved_write_mode\")\n82:         # CAURA-682 Phase 1: per-phase latency capture. The summary emit\n83:         # lives in ``_create_memory_pipeline`` after pipeline.run; each\n84:         # phase deposits its duration here.\n85:         timings: dict = ctx.data.setdefault(\"phase_timings\", {})\n86: \n87:         # write_mode-aware deferral. See the module docstring for the\n88:         # contracts each mode enforces. A cached embedding is a hit on\n89:         # the idempotency/content-hash cache (pure dict lookup, no\n90:         # provider call) so we reuse it even when hot-path embed is off\n91:         # — nothing to offload.\n92:         # Deferral driven by ``settings.deployment_mode`` via the\n93:         # ``inline_embedding`` / ``inline_enrichment`` helpers — the\n94:         # only per-deploy control after F3 Phase 3.\n95:         if resolved_write_mode == \"strong\":\n96:             defer_embedding = False\n97:             defer_enrichment = False\n98:         elif resolved_write_mode == \"fast\":\n99:             defer_embedding = (not settings.inline_embedding) and cached_embedding is None\n100:             defer_enrichment = True\n101:         else:\n102:             defer_embedding = (not settings.inline_embedding) and cached_embedding is None\n103:             defer_enrichment = not settings.inline_enrichment\n104: \n105:         embedding_task = None\n106:         if cached_embedding is not None:\n107:             logger.info(\"Reusing existing embedding for content_hash=%s\", ch[:12])\n108: \n109:             async def _return_cached():\n110:                 return cached_embedding\n111: \n112:             # ``_timed`` records a sub-millisecond duration around the\n113:             # trivial cache-return coroutine — that satisfies the\n114:             # \"key present = ran inline (≈0 ms = cached)\" contract for\n115:             # downstream log readers. Distinct from \"deferred to\n116:             # core-worker\" where the key is absent entirely.\n117:             embedding_task = _timed(_return_cached(), timings, \"embedding_ms\")\n118:         elif not defer_embedding:\n119:             embedding_task = _timed(get_embedding(data.content, tenant_config), timings, \"embedding_ms\")\n120: \n121:         enrichment_task = None\n122:         if (\n123:             not defer_enrichment\n124:             and tenant_config.enrichment_enabled\n125:             and tenant_config.enrichment_provider != \"none\"\n126:         ):\n127:             from core_api.services.memory_enrichment import enrich_memory\n128: \n129:             enrichment_task = _timed(\n130:                 enrich_memory(data.content, tenant_config, reference_datetime=data.reference_datetime),\n131:                 timings,\n132:                 \"enrichment_ms\",\n133:             )\n134: \n135:         # Gather whichever subset of tasks exists; stays parallel when\n136:         # both are present and avoids the gather overhead when only one\n137:         # is present (or neither, in the unlikely all-cached-off case).\n138:         pending = [t for t in (embedding_task, enrichment_task) if t is not None]\n139:         results: list = []\n140:         if pending:\n141:             try:\n142:                 results = await asyncio.wait_for(\n143:                     asyncio.gather(*pending),\n144:                     timeout=settings.enrichment_inline_timeout_seconds,\n145:                 )\n146:             except TimeoutError:\n147:                 # One message covers both paths — the single wait_for now\n148:                 # wraps embedding-only (flag=on, no enrichment) and\n149:                 # embedding+enrichment gather indiscriminately.\n150:                 raise HTTPException(status_code=504, detail=\"Memory write timed out (embedding/enrichment)\")\n151:         # Iterate rather than pop(0) — same effective semantics without\n152:         # mutating ``results`` as a side-effect and without the subtle\n153:         # O(n) shift that a list.pop(0) does.\n154:         result_iter = iter(results)\n155:         embedding = next(result_iter) if embedding_task is not None else None\n156:         enrichment = next(result_iter) if enrichment_task is not None else None\n157: \n158:         # Hint re-embed disabled (CAURA-222): writes embedded\n159:         # `compose_embedding_text(content, retrieval_hint)` —\n160:         # \"[Retrieval hint]: ...\\n\\n<content>\" — while queries embed raw\n161:         # text. Identical content↔query produced cosine ~0.69 instead of\n162:         # ~1.0, capping recall across dedup, entity_lookup, and search\n163:         # ranking. The background hint re-embed in\n164:         # `_enrich_memory_background` (memory_service._enrich_memory_background)\n165:         # required the same fix; it now also embeds raw `content`. Both\n166:         # sides — hot path and background — embed raw `content` to match\n167:         # the search surface (raw query through `get_query_embedding`).\n168: \n169:         ctx.data[\"embedding\"] = embedding\n170:         ctx.data[\"enrichment\"] = enrichment\n171:         return None\n\n(End of file - total 171 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Concurrent embedding + LLM enrichment via asyncio.gather.\n\nDeferral is now ``write_mode``-aware (restores the original CAURA-229\ncontract that the CAURA-524 step-consolidation + CAURA-595 PR-C global-\nflag pattern inadvertently flattened):\n\n* ``write_mode == \"strong\"`` → embed and enrich **always inline**,\n  regardless of ``settings.deployment_mode``. Strong callers\n  explicitly opted into \"thorough write before commit\"; the\n  per-deploy mode targets fast-mode latency, not strong. Running\n  inline here is what gives strong its meaningful guarantees —\n  ``CheckSemanticDuplicate`` runs against a real embedding (so the\n  409-on-near-duplicate contract holds), and the agent reads its own\n  enriched ``title`` / ``memory_type`` / ``weight`` / ``status`` /\n  ``ts_valid_*`` back in the response.\n* ``write_mode == \"fast\"`` → LLM enrichment **always deferred**\n  (matches CAURA-229's \"fast = no LLM on the request path\"\n  intent). Embedding follows ``settings.inline_embedding`` so OSS\n  local stays inline ~200ms while SaaS prod defers to ``core-worker``\n  for the sub-2s p99 visibility SLA.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/pipeline/steps/write/parallel_embed_enrich.py","text":"\"\"\"Concurrent embedding + LLM enrichment via asyncio.gather.\n\nDeferral is now ``write_mode``-aware (restores the original CAURA-229\ncontract that the CAURA-524 step-consolidation + CAURA-595 PR-C global-\nflag pattern inadvertently flattened):\n\n* ``write_mode == \"strong\"`` → embed and enrich **always inline**,\n  regardless of ``settings.deployment_mode``. Strong callers\n  explicitly opted into \"thorough write before commit\"; the\n  per-deploy mode targets fast-mode latency, not strong. Running\n  inline here is what gives strong its meaningful guarantees —\n  ``CheckSemanticDuplicate`` runs against a real embedding (so the\n  409-on-near-duplicate contract holds), and the agent reads its own\n  enriched ``title`` / ``memory_type`` / ``weight`` / ``status`` /\n  ``ts_valid_*`` back in the response.\n* ``write_mode == \"fast\"`` → LLM enrichment **always deferred**\n  (matches CAURA-229's \"fast = no LLM on the request path\"\n  intent). Embedding follows ``settings.inline_embedding`` so OSS\n  local stays inline ~200ms while SaaS prod defers to ``core-worker``\n  for the sub-2s p99 visibility SLA.\n* Any other ``write_mode`` value (and the ``None`` case the\n  enrichment-only sub-pipeline hits during extract-only / auto-chunk)\n  reads both helpers — preserves today's behaviour for those\n  branches.\n\nBehind both deferred paths: ``ScheduleBackgroundTasks`` publishes\n``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED`` / ``Topics.Memory.ENRICH_REQUESTED``\nso ``core-worker`` runs the provider call and PATCHes the row back.\nHint-based re-embed is DISABLED (CAURA-222): writes used to embed\n``compose_embedding_text(content, retrieval_hint)`` while queries embed\nraw text, producing a write/query surface asymmetry that capped recall\nacross dedup, entity-lookup, and search ranking. Until a symmetric\nreintroduction lands, both the hot-path here and the background\nre-embed in ``_enrich_memory_background`` embed raw ``content``.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport asyncio\nimport logging\nimport time\nfrom collections.abc import Awaitable\nfrom typing import Any\n\nfrom fastapi import HTTPException\n\nfrom common.embedding import get_embedding\nfrom core_api.config import settings\nfrom core_api.pipeline.context import PipelineContext\nfrom core_api.pipeline.step import StepResult\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nasync def _timed(awaitable: Awaitable[Any], timings: dict, key: str) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"Await ``awaitable`` and record its wall-clock duration into ``timings[key]``.\n\n    Used to separate embed and enrich latencies even though ``asyncio.gather``\n    runs them concurrently — without this, a slow LLM enrichment masks the\n    embedding's own latency in the gather wall-clock. The pre-/post-await\n    `perf_counter` samples each task's own time, so values are additive but\n    not exclusive (they overlap when gather runs both).\n    \"\"\"\n    t0 = time.perf_counter()\n    try:\n        return await awaitable\n    finally:\n        timings[key] = round((time.perf_counter() - t0) * 1000)\n\n\nclass ParallelEmbedEnrich:\n    @property\n    def name(self) -> str:\n        return \"parallel_embed_enrich\"\n\n    async def execute(self, ctx: PipelineContext) -> StepResult | None:\n        data = ctx.data[\"input\"]\n        tenant_config = ctx.tenant_config\n        cached_embedding = ctx.data.get(\"cached_embedding\")\n        ch = ctx.data.get(\"content_hash\")\n        resolved_write_mode = ctx.data.get(\"resolved_write_mode\")\n        # CAURA-682 Phase 1: per-phase latency capture. The summary emit\n        # lives in ``_create_memory_pipeline`` after pipeline.run; each\n        # phase deposits its duration here.\n        timings: dict = ctx.data.setdefault(\"phase_timings\", {})\n\n        # write_mode-aware deferral. See the module docstring for the\n        # contracts each mode enforces. A cached embedding is a hit on\n        # the idempotency/content-hash cache (pure dict lookup, no\n        # provider call) so we reuse it even when hot-path embed is off\n        # — nothing to offload.\n        # Deferral driven by ``settings.deployment_mode`` via the\n        # ``inline_embedding`` / ``inline_enrichment`` helpers — the\n        # only per-deploy control after F3 Phase 3.\n        if resolved_write_mode == \"strong\":\n            defer_embedding = False\n            defer_enrichment = False\n        elif resolved_write_mode == \"fast\":\n            defer_embedding = (not settings.inline_embedding) and cached_embedding is None\n            defer_enrichment = True\n        else:\n            defer_embedding = (not settings.inline_embedding) and cached_embedding is None\n            defer_enrichment = not settings.inline_enrichment\n\n        embedding_task = None\n        if cached_embedding is not None:\n            logger.info(\"Reusing existing embedding for content_hash=%s\", ch[:12])\n\n            async def _return_cached():\n                return cached_embedding\n\n            # ``_timed`` records a sub-millisecond duration around the\n            # trivial cache-return coroutine — that satisfies the\n            # \"key present = ran inline (≈0 ms = cached)\" contract for\n            # downstream log readers. Distinct from \"deferred to\n            # core-worker\" where the key is absent entirely.\n            embedding_task = _timed(_return_cached(), timings, \"embedding_ms\")\n        elif not defer_embedding:\n            embedding_task = _timed(get_embedding(data.content, tenant_config), timings, \"embedding_ms\")\n\n        enrichment_task = None\n        if (\n            not defer_enrichment\n            and tenant_config.enrichment_enabled\n            and tenant_config.enrichment_provider != \"none\"\n        ):\n            from core_api.services.memory_enrichment import enrich_memory\n\n            enrichment_task = _timed(\n                enrich_memory(data.content, tenant_config, reference_datetime=data.reference_datetime),\n                timings,\n                \"enrichment_ms\",\n            )\n\n        # Gather whichever subset of tasks exists; stays parallel when\n        # both are present and avoids the gather overhead when only one\n        # is present (or neither, in the unlikely all-cached-off case).\n        pending = [t for t in (embedding_task, enrichment_task) if t is not None]\n        results: list = []\n        if pending:\n            try:\n                results = await asyncio.wait_for(\n                    asyncio.gather(*pending),\n                    timeout=settings.enrichment_inline_timeout_seconds,\n                )\n            except TimeoutError:\n                # One message covers both paths — the single wait_for now\n                # wraps embedding-only (flag=on, no enrichment) and\n                # embedding+enrichment gather indiscriminately.\n                raise HTTPException(status_code=504, detail=\"Memory write timed out (embedding/enrichment)\")\n        # Iterate rather than pop(0) — same effective semantics without\n        # mutating ``results`` as a side-effect and without the subtle\n        # O(n) shift that a list.pop(0) does.\n        result_iter = iter(results)\n        embedding = next(result_iter) if embedding_task is not None else None\n        enrichment = next(result_iter) if enrichment_task is not None else None\n\n        # Hint re-embed disabled (CAURA-222): writes embedded\n        # `compose_embedding_text(content, retrieval_hint)` —\n        # \"[Retrieval hint]: ...\\n\\n<content>\" — while queries embed raw\n        # text. Identical content↔query produced cosine ~0.69 instead of\n        # ~1.0, capping recall across dedup, entity_lookup, and search\n        # ranking. The background hint re-embed in\n        # `_enrich_memory_background` (memory_service._enrich_memory_background)\n        # required the same fix; it now also embeds raw `content`. Both\n        # sides — hot path and background — embed raw `content` to match\n        # the search surface (raw query through `get_query_embedding`).\n\n        ctx.data[\"embedding\"] = embedding\n        ctx.data[\"enrichment\"] = enrichment\n        return None","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":171,"totalLines":171,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/pipeline/steps/write/parallel_embed_enrich.py","time":{"start":1780728124735,"end":1780728124740}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d39ef22427eb546016a23c13c9bd48191bfb2436bad2a2d7c"}},"id":"prt_e9baad526001TEG1EqsTMQKhzo","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baaa426001o76uwc3IG1Cx97"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728124746,"sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_r4HAZA6aCTVhoG5s7uTJGDsU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_embed_publisher.py","offset":1,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_embed_publisher.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Publish ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED`` events.\n2: \n3: Convenience wrapper so call sites in the write hot path don't have to\n4: re-build the ``Event`` envelope + ``MemoryEmbedRequest`` payload by hand.\n5: The helper validates the payload via Pydantic before publishing — schema\n6: drift between this caller and ``core_worker.consumer.handle_embed_request``\n7: surfaces here at publish time rather than as a runtime error inside the\n8: consumer (where it would chew through the max-delivery-attempts budget).\n9: \"\"\"\n10: \n11: from __future__ import annotations\n12: \n13: from uuid import UUID\n14: \n15: from common.events.base import Event\n16: from common.events.factory import get_event_bus\n17: from common.events.memory_embed_request import MemoryEmbedRequest\n18: from common.events.topics import Topics\n19: \n20: \n21: async def publish_memory_embed_request(\n22:     *,\n23:     memory_id: UUID,\n24:     content: str,\n25:     tenant_id: str,\n26:     content_hash: str | None = None,\n27: ) -> None:\n28:     \"\"\"Publish one embed-request event for a memory persisted with ``embedding=NULL``.\n29: \n30:     Fire-and-forget: ``bus.publish`` returns once the transport has\n31:     accepted the message (Pub/Sub) or the in-process subscriber has been\n32:     invoked (inprocess bus). Callers wrap the call in\n33:     ``track_task(tracked_task(...))`` so a transport error doesn't bubble\n34:     out of the request handler.\n35:     \"\"\"\n36:     payload = MemoryEmbedRequest(\n37:         memory_id=memory_id,\n38:         tenant_id=tenant_id,\n39:         content=content,\n40:         content_hash=content_hash,\n41:     )\n42:     event = Event(\n43:         event_type=Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED,\n44:         tenant_id=tenant_id,\n45:         payload=payload.model_dump(mode=\"json\"),\n46:     )\n47:     bus = get_event_bus()\n48:     await bus.publish(Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED, event)\n\n(End of file - total 48 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Publish ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED`` events.\n\nConvenience wrapper so call sites in the write hot path don't have to\nre-build the ``Event`` envelope + ``MemoryEmbedRequest`` payload by hand.\nThe helper validates the payload via Pydantic before publishing — schema\ndrift between this caller and ``core_worker.consumer.handle_embed_request``\nsurfaces here at publish time rather than as a runtime error inside the\nconsumer (where it would chew through the max-delivery-attempts budget).\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom uuid import UUID\n\nfrom common.events.base import Event\nfrom common.events.factory import get_event_bus\nfrom common.events.memory_embed_request import MemoryEmbedRequest\nfrom common.events.topics import Topics\n\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_embed_publisher.py","text":"\"\"\"Publish ``Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED`` events.\n\nConvenience wrapper so call sites in the write hot path don't have to\nre-build the ``Event`` envelope + ``MemoryEmbedRequest`` payload by hand.\nThe helper validates the payload via Pydantic before publishing — schema\ndrift between this caller and ``core_worker.consumer.handle_embed_request``\nsurfaces here at publish time rather than as a runtime error inside the\nconsumer (where it would chew through the max-delivery-attempts budget).\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom uuid import UUID\n\nfrom common.events.base import Event\nfrom common.events.factory import get_event_bus\nfrom common.events.memory_embed_request import MemoryEmbedRequest\nfrom common.events.topics import Topics\n\n\nasync def publish_memory_embed_request(\n    *,\n    memory_id: UUID,\n    content: str,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    content_hash: str | None = None,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Publish one embed-request event for a memory persisted with ``embedding=NULL``.\n\n    Fire-and-forget: ``bus.publish`` returns once the transport has\n    accepted the message (Pub/Sub) or the in-process subscriber has been\n    invoked (inprocess bus). Callers wrap the call in\n    ``track_task(tracked_task(...))`` so a transport error doesn't bubble\n    out of the request handler.\n    \"\"\"\n    payload = MemoryEmbedRequest(\n        memory_id=memory_id,\n        tenant_id=tenant_id,\n        content=content,\n        content_hash=content_hash,\n    )\n    event = Event(\n        event_type=Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED,\n        tenant_id=tenant_id,\n        payload=payload.model_dump(mode=\"json\"),\n    )\n    bus = get_event_bus()\n    await bus.publish(Topics.Memory.EMBED_REQUESTED, event)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":48,"totalLines":48,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/events/memory_embed_publisher.py","time":{"start":1780728124739,"end":1780728124746}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d39ef22427eb546016a23c13c9bdc8191b9ec02ca5e25e2e4"}},"id":"prt_e9baad541001MrBLu7O15SRyCM","sessionID":"ses_164567591ffeXwPyQE0CKtQKNY","messageID":"msg_e9baaa426001o76uwc3IG1Cx97"}}
